title: pecan pie
directions: Using
a
blender,
mix
all ingredients together until creamy.
Pour
into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Garnish with finely chopped pecans (optional).	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nissen salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to hot pineapple and stir until dissolved.
Chill until the mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Soften cream cheese and whip with a fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts and add to pineapple mixture.
Whip cream and fold into the salad.
Pour into mold or dish.
Keep in refrigerator.
You can add a few chopped green and/or red maraschino cherries.

title: oatmeal yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water along with 1 teaspoon sugar. Pour milk over shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 1 cup flour, then add yeast.
Stir.
Add oats and stir.
Add enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto floured board and knead until smooth and satiny adding flour as needed.
Round dough into a ball.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush lightly with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Punch down.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves and let rise.

title: diet apple crunch
directions: Sprinkle cinnamon mixture over apples, which are arranged in baking dish.
Add Grape-Nuts.
Microwave, covered, for 5 minutes on High.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt into bowl.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High until light brown about 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir 1 or 2 times.
Then
stir in remaining ingredients until light and foamy, then quickly spread onto heavily greased baking sheet.

title: brandy pie
directions: Whip the cream and slowly add powdered sugar.
Slowly add lightly beaten egg yolks,
brandy and sherry.
Add nutmeg to taste and pour mixture into prepared shell.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours. Thaw a few minutes so pie will slice easily.

title: casserole of chicken
directions: Place ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: western beef casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain well. Add tomato sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper; blend well. Spoon into a 2 1/2 to 3-quart lightly greased casserole.
Spoon corn evenly over meat mixture.
Stir green chilies into potatoes and spread over corn.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly around edges. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Top with chopped tomatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cider vinegar
directions: For a taste treat, fill glasses half full of cider.
Fill the rest with club soda or sparkling water and ice.
Garnish if desired.

title: sugar-free banana cream pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Arrange banana slices in bottom of pie shell.
Spread pie filling over bananas.
Chill.

title: amish bacon cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Serve with crackers.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix together all ingredients, then fold in Cool Whip 30 minutes before serving.
Mix well. Serve in glass bowl if possible.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and save broth for boiling spaghetti.
Remove chicken from bone and cut into medium size pieces.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in oleo.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth; drain.
Add soup, sauteed vegetables, pimento and grated cheese. Add chicken and blend gently.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake and bake as directed on box.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool, then crumble half cake in bottom of punch bowl or clear large bowl.
Layer 1/2 prepared pudding, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 jello and 1/4 Cool Whip.
Make sure everything touches sides of bowl so as to be able to see layers.
Repeat layer.
Put nuts and cherries, sliced in half, on top.
Cover completely with plastic wrap and chill all day or overnight.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil for 25 minutes.
Put in canning jars and store.

title: choyote vegetables(cho-cho)
directions: Prepare in pot the choyote (cho cho) and carrots.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add broccoli, string beans, onion and pinch of salt to taste.
Cook for about 5 or 6 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and shortening together and add water, ginger, salt and soda.
Add flour to stiffen so you can roll out (not too stiff), dough should be sticky.
Bake at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Measure and pour all ingredients into saucepan.
Place on medium to high heat and bring to boil.
Lower heat immediately and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: sausage-sauerkraut casserole
directions: Cook and drain fat off of sausage.
Prepare 4 to 6 servings of mashed potatoes.
Place drained sauerkraut in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage on top.
Cover with potatoes.
Shake Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Next, mix cornstarch with the milk.
Put corn and milk together.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pink champagne
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar.
Blend well with spoon.
Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon in casserole dish.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs; add pineapple and bread.
Bake in 2-quart buttered Pyrex dish at 350° for 1 hour. Can be served hot or cold.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup with chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Mix milk with Bisquick and pour over top of casserole.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: grandma bly's old fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well; set aside.
In a separate bowl, pour milk and add vinegar.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Alternate flour and sour cream in shortening mixture; stir well.
Drop onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cookie decorations or colored sugar crystals.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown around edges.

title: salmon loaf with green pea sauce
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of margarine. Add onion and celery and cook until soft, 5 minutes.
Blend 1 tablespoon of flour; add milk and cook 3 to 5 minutes, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salmon, bread crumbs, egg white, 1 teaspoon dill, 2 teaspoons of lemon juice and 1/8 teaspoon black pepper.
Turn all in a greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix ketchup, oil, sugar, vinegar and salt well; add a bit of garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce to taste.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple, gelatins and lemon juice.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool mixture until it begins to thicken.
Stir in Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish; congeal.

title: sally's low-fat oatmeal cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet (olive oil or spray).
Cream oil and sugar together.
Add egg white, vanilla, water, oats, flours, baking soda and cinnamon until blended (do not overmix).
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: deluxe pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Stir into the dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add melted butter.
When griddle has reached the correct temperature, pour the cakes.
When full of bubbles, turn.
Be sure to turn cakes only once.
Serve hot with butter and maple syrup.

title: sunday nite specials
directions: Preheat the frankfurters in hot water; split and place on toasted bread.
Sprinkle chopped onion and Cheddar cheese on; spread spaghetti sauce all over and heat in toaster oven or regular oven until bubbly.
This makes a quick and tasty main dish.
Easy way to feed unexpected company.

title: sensation salad dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in a quart jar.
Dressing will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.
Very good tossed lettuce, water cress, fresh spinach, Swiss chard and parsley leaves.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Brown chicken in butter and place in a baking dish.
Blend wine, broth and parsley; set aside.
Bake chicken in oven for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Place in serving dish.
Top with nuts and serve with apple wedges.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each.
Add flour, salt, and pineapple; mix well.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Bake in tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and spices.
Beat well.
Blend in pie mix.
Add milk.
Beat well.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat
cheese
until
fluffy;
beat
in	Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Fold
in whipped cream.
Turn into crust.
Drizzle syrup over pie and swirl.
Chill 4 hours.

title: mother's knobby apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples and pecans, with mixer. Add apples and pecans.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 12 medium muffin cups. Mix all ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon sugar over batter in each cup.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.

title: shut your face stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and discard.
Mix crabmeat, breadcrumbs, egg white, garlic, lemon juice and butter until thoroughly blended.
Stuff mushroom caps to overflowing and place on a slightly greased cookie sheet.
Cut cheese into squares (about size and thickness of an M&M) and press into each mushroom. Bake at 400 degrees for 10-15 minutes.
Mushrooms should shrink and stuffing should brown.
Serve with cold beer, wine or gin martinis.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture, beating well.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans and apples.

title: eggplant italiano
directions: Lightly grease bottom of 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom with thin layer of spaghetti sauce.
Layer eggplant, 1/2 teaspoon parsley flakes, onion, 1/2 of spaghetti sauce, 1/2 of Italian bread crumbs and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and bread crumbs.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of butter until soft.
Mix into bread crumb mixture. Add salt and spices.
Add meat and mix thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour to let flavors blend and mixture thicken.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Brown slowly in remaining butter, turning carefully so balls hold their shape.
Place meat balls in a large casserole or Dutch oven.
Add flour to drippings in pan.
Brown and stir in bouillon.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add half and half, salt and pepper to taste and crushed dill weed. Sauce is very thin.
Stir in sauce over meat balls.
Bake in oven at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.
Good over noodles or rice or as hors d'oeuvres.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except the coconut.
Roll into balls. Roll in coconut.

title: three layer chocolate salad
directions: First Layer:
Melt butter and add to flour and chopped nuts. Mix and press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and garlic.
Brown hamburger and sausage.
Pour off grease.
Add tomatoes, paste, sauce and puree. Add oregano to taste (2 to 3 teaspoons).
Add 6 bay leaves.
Add mushrooms. Cook at least 6 hours.
Pour off grease.
Remove bay leaves and serve over noodles.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate for one hour.
Put on rotisserie and cook for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt vanilla ice cream to semi-solid (or just able to pour), and place in bottom of angel food cake pan until it is 1/2 to 3/4 inch thickness.
Return this to freezer until re-frozen.
In meantime, freeze scoops of your favorite sherbet on a separate dish or pan.
When both of above are frozen, place sherbet on top of ice cream and re-freeze.
Melt more vanilla ice cream and pour over sherbet and re-freeze.
(If you wish, you may add another layer - always end with vanilla ice cream).
When above is re-frozen, may add topping (Example:
Cool Whip to which food coloring may be added).
Then re-freeze again.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in a large pot of boiling water for 20 minutes or until tender. Peel potatoes and mash. Add sour cream, cream cheese, salt, pepper, dill and onion. Place mixture in baking dish. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: linguine vegetable salad(one serving)
directions: In medium bowl, combine linguine, snow peas, zucchini, chickpeas and tomatoes; set aside.

title: broccoli-chicken alfredo
directions: Using a large nonstick skillet, saute chicken, broccoli, onions and garlic over medium heat until onions are clear and chicken is browned.
Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is done. Salt and pepper to taste.
Microwave cream cheese to soften then add cream, basil, oregano and mix until smooth.
Add sauce to chicken mixture and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until smooth, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
Serve over pasta of your choice.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Beat eggs and add sugar, shortening and salt.
Beat well.
Add yeast and water.
Add 3 cups flour, 1 cup at a time.
Beat well. Stir in remaining flour.
Let rise 3 hours or until doubled in bulk at room temperature.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: *Poppy seed substitutes nicely for celery seed.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well and lightly flour a Bundt pan.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter and saute rice; add beef consomme, mushrooms, water, onions and oregano.
Bake in a covered casserole dish for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients today.
Chill overnight for a better flavor.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine string beans, soup, almonds and cheese.
Top with onion rings and bake in a 200° oven until bubbly.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown sausages and drain.
Cut up cheese and melt on low heat. Stir in sausage and seasoning.
Spread on bread and bake on cookie sheets at 300° for 10 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
May be frozen and use as needed.

title: mean beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients in large baking casserole dish.
Stir well and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: yogurt jammies(muffins)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Make a "well" in center and mix in egg, melted butter, milk, yogurt and vanilla (may use vanilla yogurt and omit vanilla).
Grease muffin tins and fill 1/4 full with mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon preserves or 5 whole blueberries.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: yogurt vegetable dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese with fork in small bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except yogurt, and mix well.
Fold in yogurt.
Cover and chill.

title: maui chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Transfer chicken to slow cooker. Combine remaining ingredients, pour over chicken.
Cover.
Cook on high 4 - 6 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Bake in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan, according to cake directions.
Let cool.
Drain pineapple well.
Spread on top of cake.
Whip together milk, cream cheese and packages of pudding.
Spread mixture over (cake) pineapple on cake.
Let set up a little.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix together ingredients and place in small baking dish or microwavable container.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350° or 5 to 10 minutes in microwave on High until bubbly and lightly browned.
Serve with crackers (preferably rye or pumpernickel). Then as everyone is raving over this dish, don't tell them what's in it or how easy it was to make.
This way you will get invited to every party and asked to bring the cheese dip.
If you give away the recipe, you may have to stay home.

title: chicken pot pie filling
directions: Heat margarine over low heat.
Blend flour, onion, salt and pepper; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute. Add chicken and vegetables.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat together eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients, hand mixing just to combine.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Spread batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mixture will be stiff and sticky; push into corners.
Bake for 35 minutes. Remove from pan to wire rack to cool.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: date nut bread
directions: Add 1 cup dates and 1 teaspoon soda to boiling water.
Cool and set aside.
Mix shortening, sugar, vanilla, egg and flour together.
Add chopped dates.
Pour date mixture into flour mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a loaf pan.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk and bring to a boil. Stirring constantly, boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; put in chocolate morsels and cream.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: low-fat sloppy joes
directions: Brown chuck, then drain off fat.
Mix together remaining ingredients (except pepper).
Simmer until hot, then cut up pepper in mixture.
Keep in crock-pot until time of serving.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix well together the first 4 ingredients.
Sift the remaining and add.
Mix well.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: date cake
directions: Mix dates with boiling water and cool to lukewarm.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Combine with date mixture, then add flour, sifted with salt and soda.
Beat until well mixed and add nut meats.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch cake pan in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage, chili and cheese tartlets
directions: Cook sausage in heavy large skillet over medium heat until no longer pink, breaking up with fork.
Drain off fat; add salsa, cheeses and green chilies to skillet and simmer until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chicken and yellow rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bone; save broth.
Place chicken in large deep casserole dish.
Mix soup, broth and water. To this, add rice, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over chicken. Top with margarine that has been sliced.
Cover with heavy foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Place chops in single layer in pan, put sliced potatoes around chops. Mix soup mix, soup, salt and pepper and pour over chops and potatoes. Cover pan with foil and bake for 1 - 1 1/2 hour, uncovering last 15 minutes.

title: michael's chocolate pie
directions: Slice banana on bottom of pie shell.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over banana.
Mix chocolate pudding and pour over chocolate and banana in pie shell. Mix the vanilla pudding and spread on top of chocolate pudding or put vanilla pudding in the center.
Chill and serve with whipped cream or make a meringue for top of pie.

title: filled meat loaf roll
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Add ground meat, onion, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Mix well on waxed paper.
Pat mixture into a 12 x 8-inch size.
Arrange salami slices to cover meat. Top with chopped spinach (thawed and squeezed dry) and cheese. Starting at narrow end, roll in jelly roll fashion, lifting wax paper to help shape roll.
Place in pan seam side down.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
When loaf starts to brown, cover loosely with tent of folded foil to prevent oven browning.

title: never fail recipe for cupcakes(makes 18 to 20 cupcakes)
directions: Put in bowl in order given.
Mix after last item is added; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost.

title: warm shrimp and artichoke spread
directions: Stir together chopped shrimp and chopped artichoke hearts; mix in mayonnaise and hot sauce. Place in shallow casserole dish. Sprinkle with Romano cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve warm with baked pita chips or your favorite deli bread broken into pieces.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and slice each apple into eight slices.
Pull apart each biscuit into 3 layers.
Wrap each apple slice with 1/3 of a biscuit.
Place wrapped apples in a greased baking dish.
Bring water, sugar and margarine to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over wrapped apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; work in shortening until consistency of cornmeal.
Mix egg yolk, milk and vanilla; add to dry ingredients to make soft dough.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on floured canvas cloth.
Take fingers and spread with unbeaten egg white.
Cut into small squares and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cover top of squares with nutmeats and press them down.
Bake at 350°; watch carefully.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until it resembles meal. Spread 3/4 of mixture on pie crust.
Cook cornstarch, sugar, salt, milk, egg yolks, butter and vanilla until thick.
Pour into pie shell on top of peanut butter mixture.
Top with meringue and sprinkle with remaining peanut butter mixture.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan; simmer for 20 minutes.
For best taste results, make a day ahead and reheat.

title: green bean bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper. Stir in drained green beans and half of the onions, Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir well; top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In a large pot, boil chicken, onion and celery until the chicken is done.
Take out the chicken; allow it to cool while cooking rice in the water that you used to cook the chicken.
When the rice is done, add broccoli, the boned chopped chicken, cream of mushroom soup and cheese.
Top with cheese and put in warm oven until the cheese is melted and the broccoli is warm.

title: punch
directions: Combine juices and sweetener.
Pour ginger ale in just before serving.

title: easy chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: In large saucepan, boil chicken in water for 10 to 12 minutes. (Leftover chicken may be substituted for boiling chicken.)
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups together.
Pour over chicken.
Cook stuffing according to package directions; then layer on top of mixture.
Arrange broccoli on top (if frozen, defrost and drain off water).
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pistachio pineapple fluff
directions: Combine pineapple, juice and all; add pistachio pudding.
Mix well.
Mix in Cool Whip and a few chopped maraschino cherries and crushed Heath bar.	Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight before serving.

title: horsey sauce
directions: Mix all well. Keep refrigerated and tightly covered to use in 2 weeks. Do not freeze. Serves 1.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil water, whole cloves, cinnamon and tea or tea bags for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes.
Remove cloves, cinnamon and tea bags.
Add sugar, juice of oranges or lemonade, pineapple juice and juice of lemons.
Serve hot.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix dissolved yeast, sugar, eggs and warm water.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Let rise 8 hours or overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add 3/4 cup of water and all of taco mix, but 1 tablespoon.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cool. Combine torn lettuce, tomatoes, beans, cheese, meat and chips in a very large bowl.
Combine the Thousand Island dressing, sugar and 1 tablespoon taco seasoning mix.
Stir and pour over salad.
Mix thoroughly.
Don't add chips or dressing until ready to serve.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into small balls.
Blend soup and water; heat in pressure pan until mixture begins to simmer.
Add the meatballs to the soup.
Cook at 15 pounds pressure 10 minutes.

title: homemade granola cereal
directions: Heat oatmeal in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (sprayed with a no-stick spray) at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix and stir in oil, honey, almonds and coconut. Return to 325° oven and bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Take out and stir every 10 minutes while baking. Browns nicely.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and store in refrigerator.
Keeps for weeks.
Very good with milk as cereal or as a snack food.

title: anne's chicken
directions: Wash chicken; brush with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in slow cooker.
Sprinkle dry salad mix over all. Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours.
Mix soup, cheese, wine and onion.
Pour over chicken in pot and cook 30 minutes more.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet. Add flour and stir until blended. Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook until tender. Add crawfish and cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
It may even take 15 to 20 minutes to cook. Add spices.
Cover and simmer until seasonings are blended (very low heat).
Serve over rice.

title: crab and artichoke au gratin
directions: In large skillet saute mushrooms, shallots and celery in butter.
Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Mix mayonnaise and cream with crab in bowl.
Stir in eggs, sherry and artichokes.
Add mushrooms to crab mixture.
Pour mixture into individual serving shells or au gratin dishes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.
Assembly: 30 minutes.
Bake:
30 minutes.

title: casserole
directions: Mix vegetables.
Put in baking dish.
Brown meat and spread on top.
Save green peas and liquid and mix with soup.
Pour soup mixture over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potluck beans
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and drain.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and ketchup; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into a large roasting pan and add all remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yogurt pancakes(yield: 8 portions)
directions: 1. Mix together egg and the yogurt.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pat the crust into pie pan and use crust as desired.

title: communion bread (crackers)
directions: Cut flour, shortening and salt together thoroughly.
Add cold water.
Using a fork, mix well and divide into 3 or 4 equal parts and roll on floured board "very" thin.
Using an 8-inch plate, cut into circle.
Using back of butter knife, score "slightly" into 1/4's and prick all over with fork.
Put into 8-inch round cake pan.
Cut the same size circle of wax paper or parchment paper then cover bread with paper and put about 2 cups of dry rice onto paper and spread to edges of paper.
Bake each circle of bread for 8 to 10 minutes.
(The rice on the paper keeps the dough from bubbling.)

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 1 teaspoon or whatever strength you like to a cup of hot water.

title: french toast
directions: In a shallow dish, beat eggs until well blended.
Add milk, pepper and cinnamon, stirring constantly.

title: spicy hot grapefruit(microwave)
directions: Cut grapefruit in half.
Using a sharp knife, cut around the edges of the fruit between the flesh and the pith.
Then cut down between each segment, removing the skin from the flesh.
Take the core between finger and thumb and pull out, removing the skin. Remove any pits.
Sprinkle allspice over each grapefruit half. Arrange in circle and cook on High for 3 to 4 minutes until hot.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple well and place in bottom of large, flat casserole dish that has been greased.
Mix sugar, flour and shredded cheese together well and sprinkle on top of pineapple. Crush a roll of Ritz crackers and sprinkle over flour mixture. Melt margarine and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: vegetable beef stew
directions: Cook beef in hot oil in a large Dutch oven until brown. Add remaining
ingredients.
Bring
to
a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add additional
water
during
cooking if necessary.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken; remove from broth and cut into small pieces.
Add to broth 1 can of cream of chicken soup, egg noodles, peas, salt and pepper.
Add chicken; simmer until noodles are done.
Serve over egg bread.

title: stir 'n roll biscuits(serves 16 to 18)
directions: Heat oven to 475° (very hot).
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour Wesson oil and milk into a measuring cup (don't stir), then pour all at once into flour.
Stir with a fork until mixture cleans sides of bowl and rounds up into a ball.

title: frances' pecan pie
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add all other ingredients, adding pecans last.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn oven temperature down to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes more or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: mexican turkey bake
directions: Brown turkey in a large skillet; add onion, tomatoes and spices.
Cook 10 minutes.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with rice.
Top with turkey mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: beef or turkey jerky
directions: Mix first four ingredients, then let mixture stand for 5 minutes.
Place in bowl with tight seal and let stand for 10 more minutes, while you are cutting beef or turkey.
Makes enough for 4 pounds of beef or turkey.
Place meat into marinade, secure lid and let it stand for 10 more minutes.
Shake bowl and turn it every few minutes to cover all meat.
Drain.
Place on trays and dry in dehydrator.
Set vents on top and bottom to fully open.
Normal drying time is 24 to 48 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and allow to sit at room temperature for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Yields 6 servings.

title: spinach dip in pumpernickel bread
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Chop water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients (except bread) together.
Scoop out bread.
Cut into small pieces (for dipping).
Put dip into bread shell.
Arrange pieces of bread around plate.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in unbaked pie shell (deep dish) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Place pecan halves on top of pie before baking.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Boil shrimp and save stock.
Make a roux by browning the flour in heavy skillet and adding oil.
Add onions and green peppers; cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup hot stock from shrimp.
Cook and stir 15 minutes more.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 1 hour.
Stir often.
Add shrimp last 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Add more stock or seasoning if desired.

title: sam's stuffed manicotti with meat sauce
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat; add rest of ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.

title: apple-oatmeal crumbles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: ground beef croissants
directions: Brown ground beef in 12-inch skillet; drain well.
In same skillet saute white and green onions until tender.
Add ground beef.
Stuff and roll mixture in each crescent roll.
Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Heat milk and soup in a 1-quart saucepan.
Stir occasionally.
Pour hot creamy mixture over rolls. Sprinkle on cheese and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: quick fruit cake
directions: Mix.
Grease a 5 x 10-inch pan. Cook 1 hour at 300°.

title: caesar salad
directions: Place oil, pepper, lemon juice, egg and grated cheese in bowl. Use a garlic press to squeeze garlic juice into mixture.
Mix dressing with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Tear lettuce into pieces and place in bowl. Add croutons and dressing and sprinkle with cheese.
Remember to toss well.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Spread undrained pineapple over bottom of pan. Add layer of blueberries and sprinkle with sugar. Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit. Drizzle with melted butter (cover as nearly as possible). Add chopped nuts and sprinkle lightly with sugar. Bake in preheated 350° oven 45 minutes or until done. After baking about 30 minutes, take a knife and cut down to the bottom of the pan in several places to permit juice to come up through the cake.

title: spiced apple turnovers
directions: See recipe for Safflower Pastry under Breads, Rolls and Pastries.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Then take chicken off of bones and put chicken back in pot.
Bring pot to a boil.
Add lasagne noodles.
Break noodles into small pieces first.
Stir often to avoid sticking.
Turn pot to low after about 15 minutes.
Put lid on pot.
Let simmer.
Remember to stir about every 5 minutes until noodles are done.

title: summer stir-fry
directions: Melt butter and garlic. Stir-fry vegetables 5 minutes. Add milk and basil. Stir in Velveeta. Cover and simmer until cheese melts and sauce thickens. Add rotini pasta; cover and let set.

title: squash casserole
directions: In
casserole
dish, melt margarine and mix with stuffing. Remove
cup of stuffing for top of casserole.	Line bottom of	casserole with remaining stuffing.
Add squash and other ingredients.
Spread
the
cup stuffing on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Melt the box of brown sugar and the 2 sticks of oleo over low heat.
Remove and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well with beater; pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shanty creek's peanut butter pie
directions: Combine the above and pat into 9-inch pie tin.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart covered microwave-safe bowl.
Add all other ingredients, except soda, and stir well.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 30 seconds; remove and stir.
Microwave another 30 seconds; remove and stir.
Microwave for 4 minutes and 45 seconds, uncovered, on High.
Remove from oven and stir in soda.
Stir well.

title: white chili bistro(turkey chili)
directions: In a large kettle, cook the onion and the garlic in the oil over moderately low heat.
Add the cumin and cook, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add the ground turkey and cubed turkey and cook over moderate heat, stirring until the turkey is no longer pink.

Add the barley, chickpeas, jalapeno pepper, broth, marjoram and savory; simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes. Stir the arrowroot mixture, add it to the chili and simmer, uncovered, stirring for 15 minutes.
Season the chili with salt and pepper.
Serve in bowls and sprinkle with Monterey cheese and the scallions.
Makes 15 cups, serving 8 to 10.

title: cajun chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (glass pan, 9 x 13-inch).
Put chicken breasts in glass dish (large).
Sprinkle Cajun spice over chicken. Put onions, pepper, carrots, potatoes and celery.
Add salt and pepper to all of this.
Put aluminum foil over the top of pan before cooking.
Cook 1 hour on 375°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Good with beef, pork or chicken.
Yield:
About 1 1/2 cups. Approximate calories/serving:
1/2 cup = 95, 1 tablespoon = 25.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Roll chicken pieces in flour mixture to coat.
Fry in skillet in hot oil until browned on all sides.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Melt
cocoa with margarine and set aside to cool.
Beat eggs until
fluffy
and
add sugar gradually.
Beat in flour, salt
and vanilla.
Fold in cocoa mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes
in
a
greased
x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Can add chopped walnuts if desired.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Melt Crisco, peanut butter and butterscotch chips in a large saucepan over very low heat.
Pour corn flakes into a large bowl and pour hot butterscotch mixture over the flakes.
Stir until flakes are well coated.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon out mixture into mounds on wax paper lined baking sheets. Refrigerate until firm.

title: southern raised biscuits
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water.
Let stand for a few minutes, then stir.
Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup soft butter.
Add yeast and mix well.
Roll 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter and place on cookie sheet. Brush with melted butter.
Beat egg yolk and 1 tablespoon water together.
Brush on biscuits.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake in preheated hot oven (425°) about 10 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen biscuits.

title: sour cream pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust as you would a regular pizza or use a prepacked pizza crust.
Put sour cream (or plain yogurt) on crust (as you would pizza sauce).
Spread on Mozzarella cheese over sour cream.
Then add the green pepper, olives and dill (spread dill generously over pizza). You can add other toppings if you wish. Bake in oven for about 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets with part of stems and roots still on.
Remove stems and slice if large.
Measure beets.
Recipe is for 5 quarts beets.
Two tablespoons mixed spices may be added also.
Make syrup of sugar, vinegar and water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add beets, heat through, lift from syrup and pack into jars.
Pour boiling syrup over beets and seal jars with boiling lids.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Set aside 1/2 can of soup.
Mix remainder of soup, ground beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, salt and pepper together.
Put this mixture into a 9-inch deep pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Then add mashed potatoes and shredded cheese.
Top with other half or mushroom soup.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Sausage and cheese need to be at room temperature.
Work together with your hands all ingredients.
Roll into small 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chewy walnut squares
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Sift together the egg and brown sugar.
Quickly stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add walnuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients well.
Mix all together.
Drop on a cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 12 minutes or until done.

title: microwave taco casserole
directions: In a casserole dish spread refried beans over bottom, then add fried and drained ground beef.
Mix together onion, tomato sauce, 8 ounces cheese and taco seasoning.
Pour over meat.
Microwave for 10 minutes on Full powder, then garnish on the diagonal lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and black olive; repeat across.
Serve with taco chips.
Sour cream may be used on diagonal.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Drop onto wax paper.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco together; add sugar, then eggs, about 2 at a time, mixing after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add to mixture alternating with milk and flour.
Add vanilla last.
Put in bundt pan and cook at 350 degrees for about one hour.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain grease.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Add sausage and cheese.
Cut bread into chunks and layer casserole dish.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Prepare jello according to package instructions.
Let set up partially in refrigerator.
Put 1/2 of the vanilla wafer crumbs on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix jello, pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts well.
Pour into pan and cover with remaining wafer crumbs.
Chill until completely firm.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Cook ground beef (turkey) until browned and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer (uncovered) for 10 minutes.
Great with plain rice.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in cranberry with oranges and pineapple, nuts, and apple. Pour into mold.

title: chew bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion and meat. Add soup and seasonings and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and margarine to rolling boil. Remove from heat and add flour, stirring vigorously, until it forms a ball. Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously until smooth. Spread on a 15 x 11-inch jelly roll pan (greased on bottom only). Bake 30 minutes at 400°. Cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Fold in soda-vinegar mixture (do not beat).
Pour batter into two greased 9-inch pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fresh apple pudding
directions: Pour sugar over oleo.
Sift flour, soda and spices.
Mix with apples.
Add beaten eggs.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes or until done.

title: creamy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet; press with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Cut meat in bite size pieces.
Do not brown meat!
Pour undiluted soup over meat and mix until all meat is covered.
Put in a 2-quart covered casserole dish.
Bake 3 hours in a 325° oven. Stir halfway through baking time.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks good.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Break egg into mixing bowl and beat until mixed.
Add can of sweetened condensed milk, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Stir until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in the thawed dessert topping.

title: ma's hermits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can roll out and cut with a cookie cutter or can be dropped by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blonde brownies with chocolate chunks
directions: Combine baking bar and butter in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat until melted.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl, stirring until blended.
Add butter mixture, mixing well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into butter mixture.
Fold in pecans and chocolate. Spoon into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper in skillet.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and place in large 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: southern fried green tomatoes(makes 6 servings)
directions: Dip eggplant slices into egg; coat with crumbs. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Cook eggplant in 3 batches until browned, 2 minutes each side; add oil as needed. Transfer to plate. Let skillet cool slightly; wipe clean. Spread 3/4 cup marinara sauce in skillet; arrange half of eggplant on top.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk as directed on package.
Stir in thawed Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer sliced bananas, pudding mixture and vanilla wafers.
Repeat.
Put in a 13 1/2 x 9-inch dish. Chill and serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze overnight or 7 hours.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Cut
elephant
into bite-sized pieces.	Add brown gravy and cook at 465° for about 4 weeks.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix fruit with marshmallows, sour cream and coconut.
Mix lightly with fork, then chill.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour.
Add dry ingredients to flour.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk. Mix until moistened.
May be rolled out and cut into biscuits. Place in greased baking pan.
Allow to rise about an hour before baking.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 18 minutes.
(Dough may be stored in plastic in refrigerator for several days.)

title: evelyns chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour bundt pans and line bottom of bundt pan with wax paper cut to fit the bottom of the pan. Set aside. Mix the cake per box directions. Pour in lined bundt pan and bake on 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes. While the cake is baking make the frosting.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Into large bowl, measure 1 1/2 cups sugar and remaining ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Shape dough into ball; wrap and refrigerate dough 2 to 3 hours until easy to handle.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
For crisp cookies, roll dough paper thin.
For softer cookies, roll 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
With floured 2 1/2-inch round cookie cutter, cut into circles.
Re-roll trimmings and cut.
Place cookies 1 inch apart on cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with sugar or a topping.
Bake 8 minutes or until light brown.
With spatula, remove cookies to wire racks; cool.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an oblong pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake until golden brown, about 35 minutes.
Good warm or cold.

title: acapulco casserole
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet until brown, then drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Cook, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Place 1 tortilla in a round, 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1 cup beef mixture.
Repeat layers until all tortillas are used.
Pour remaining beef mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: marinated coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage. Finely shred pepper. Combine preceding in large bowl. Set aside. In 1-quart stainless saucepan, combine vinegar, oil, sugar, dry mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper. Boil over moderate heat 3 minutes to dissolve sugar. Pour over cabbage mixture and toss. Let stand 30 to 60 minutes, tossing occasionally.

title: cheese bread("grass bread")
directions: Combine milk and egg.
Add Bisquick mix, parsley, onion and half of shredded cheese. Pour into greased 8-inch or 9-inch round pan.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and mayonnaise in a mixing bowl with mixer. Add 1 cup of water and mix for 1 minute.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in oven.
Spray pan with Pam (12 1/2 x 10 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch pan).
Use Mrs. King's Icing.

title: gumdrop bread
directions: Beat eggs; combine with remaining ingredients.
Put into 2 greased loaf pans; let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy veggie salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour salad dressing over and toss to coat evenly.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Heat soup and Velveeta in saucepan.
Put cabbage in buttered dish (larger than 2 1/2 quart).
Pour heated sauce over cabbage.

title: hearty lentil soup
directions: In large kettle, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover; simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Remove ham hocks, cut meat off bones and return meat to soup.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash saute
directions: Heat margarine in large skillet over medium heat.
Cook yellow squash, zucchini and onions until just tender.
Stir in honey and brown sugar.
Serve at once.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
In bowl, mix cooked rice, cooked broccoli, cheese and soup and add onions.
Spray casserole dish with Pam and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown the chuck meat and neck bones in olive oil on a medium-high flame in a saucepan.
When done, place meat to the side and put the juices from the cooked meat into a large saucepan.
Add the garlic and onion in the large saucepan with meat juices, stirring, on a medium-high flame until the garlic and onion are browned.
Add to the large saucepan, the tomatoes, tomato paste, 4 small cans of water, the basil, oregano and Italian seasoning, salt and cooked meat.
Stir on high flame; bring to a boil.
Cover the saucepan; lower temperature to low and simmer for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
If you wish, place cooked sausage and/or meatballs in sauce about 1/2 hour before done.

title: fiddlehead soup
directions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over high heat. Add the fiddleheads; return to a boil and cook until they are almost tender and turn a slightly pale green, 5 to 8 minutes. Drain and rinse with cold water.
Coarsely chop; save.

title: sweet dough
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, then add rest of ingredients.
You may have to use more flour until dough gets easy to roll out.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Add buttermilk.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Bake as few or as many biscuits as you need at one time.
Keeps up to 2 weeks.
Pinch off dough and bake in greased muffin pans.
Rising is optional.
Bake 10 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: baked chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange in glass dish.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients over chicken, tossing to coat. Marinate, covered, for 5 hours to overnight, turning frequently. Place and marinate in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.
Serves 12.

title: baked stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers; halve and remove seeds.
Parboil for 2 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain.
Meat should be put through the food chopper with the onion.
Combine with the rice and season to taste.
Fill peppers; dot with butter and place in a shallow pan. Bake in a moderately hot oven (375°) for about 30 minutes.

title: seafood souffle
directions: Melt butter in saucepan without browning; add onions and stir at low heat 2 minutes.
Add curry powder and flour; stir until thoroughly blended.
Add milk; cook and stir over medium heat until creamy.
To sauce add salt and pepper, rice and seafood of your choice.
Stir until well mixed.
Cover and let cool 10 minutes.
Add slightly beaten yolks, stirring briskly.
Beat egg whites stiff not dry.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Line bottom
of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with dried beef. Mix all
other	ingredients except chicken and bacon.
Roll up chicken breasts
and
wrap with slice of bacon.
Use toothpick to hold together.
Pour sauce over meat.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover
and bake 1/2 hour longer.	(May be prepared and frozen before baking.)

title: five-vegetable slaw
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the cabbage, red and green bell peppers, cucumber and scallions.
Mix in the mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for up to 2 days.

title: hungarian pinched noodles
directions: Sift flour and salt into a mixing bowl.
Make a well and break in egg.
Add a little water, enough to make a soft dough.
Mix well and knead until smooth.
On a lightly floured pastry board, roll out 1/8-inch thick.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on the box; pour over nuts and coconut after placing nuts and coconut in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend together the cream cheese and confectioners sugar; spoon over cake mix.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: steamed shrimp
directions: In a saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil. Add shrimp and stir gently.
Cover.
Steam until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Remove shells and vein on back.
Serve with rice.

title: ground pea stew\(a favorite in far off countries)
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove stock to another container.
Add mushrooms, seasoning and eggs to chicken.
Pour in ground pea stock and boil over medium heat until mixture becomes thick.
Serve over rice.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add onion and stir thoroughly. Add oil SLOWLY, beating constantly, and continue to beat until thick. Add poppy seeds and beat a few minutes.

title: rice a la grecque casserole
directions: In an earthenware casserole dish fitted with a cover, saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter until the onion is soft, but not brown.
Add rice, mushrooms, tomatoes, salt, garlic and pepper. Combine the mixture thoroughly with chicken stock.

Cover the casserole tightly; bring to a boil and cook the rice in a hot oven for 20 to 25 minutes at 375° or can be cooked on top of stove. Separate the grains of rice and release the steam by tossing with a long-tined fork.
Mix in peas, raisins, 1 tablespoon of butter and pimiento.
Serve with chicken or veal.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apricot preserve bread
directions: Mix together, adding the preserves and nuts last.
Bake in tube pan or 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done when tested with a toothpick.
If the toothpick comes out clean, the bread is done.

title: layer lettuce salad
directions: Arrange in layers in order given until you have 2 layers.
Do not mix.
Now take peas out of freezer; do not cook.
Immediately sprinkle them over the above.
With spatula spread mayonnaise over peas.
Next, sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Spread Velveeta cheese over sugar and over top spread bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: brisket
directions: Sprinkle both sides with seasoned pepper, meat tenderizer, cream of mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Refrigerate overnight. Put in slow cooker and cook on low heat all day for dinner.

title: microwave swedish crunch
directions: Combine walnuts and almonds in 2-quart (12 x 17-inch) glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for about 2 minutes or until hot. Beat egg white in a small mixing bowl until stiff peaks form. Beat in sugar and salt. Stir in hot nuts. Set aside.
Place butter in 2-quart (12 x 7-inch) glass baking dish.
Microwave for about 1 minute on Roast or until melted. Add cinnamon (if desired) to nut mixture and mix.

Spread nut mixture into melted butter and microwave on Roast for 6 minutes. Stir well and continue cooking on Roast for an additional 5 minutes or until glazed. Stir well and let stand 10 minutes until cool and hardened.
Break apart and serve.

title: lasagne, shortcut style
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add the next 4 ingredients; cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Salt to taste.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Place half the noodles in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cover with a third of the sauce.
Add half the
Mozzarella, then half the cottage cheese. Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix the zucchini (and excess liquid), egg, vanilla, flour, sugar, butter and milk in a blender until thoroughly mixed.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake pie for 20 minutes at 450°.
Lower the oven temperature to 350° and bake for 10 minutes more.
Let cool completely before serving. Serves 8.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Wash and cut up chicken in several pieces.
Put chicken in Dutch
oven and boil for 45 minutes.
Take chicken out and set aside.
Cut
biscuits in half; drop in chicken broth with poultry seasonings	and
thin
sliced
onions.
Let
cook for approximately
minutes.
Put
chicken back in pot with the biscuits and broth.
Cook for approximately 5 minutes.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Wrap in foil and smoke 5 hours.
Take off foil last hour to brown.
If larger turkey is desired, smoke 30 minutes per pound.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Form into small balls in hands.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 40 to 45 minutes in a 300° oven.
Cookies will not be brown on top when done.
Roll in confectioners sugar when cooled a little. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend shortening, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in flour and form into balls the size of walnuts. Place on a greased cookie sheet and press both ways with a fork. Bake at 400° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix vinegar or lemon juice, sugar and cornstarch.
Heat oil; add ketchup and rest of ingredients, stirring lightly, until thickened and boiling.
Refrigerate.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Spread 1 1/4 cups cookie crumbs in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream butter, powdered sugar and vanilla until fluffy; beat in yolks separately.
Carefully spread mixture over crumbs.
Beat cream stiff; fold in drained pineapple, and spread carefully over butter-cookie layer.
Top with remaining cookie crumbs.
Cover with waxed paper.
Chill several hours.
Cut in squares.
Serves 12.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan.
Add the milk and egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add coconut and vanilla and cool.
Pour into pie shell.

title: trucker's turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 2-quart dish. Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or microwave on High power 15 to 20 minutes. Check after 7 minutes and turn dish.

title: lo-carb-cal mousse
directions: Mix. Fold into greased pie pan.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill or freeze.
Top with whipped cream and serve.
Good made with different puddings.

title: batter for fruit and vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip fruit or vegetables.

title: honey sweet pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until skins slip off easily.
Put into cold water. Remove skins, tops and roots.

title: strawberry yogurt
directions: Blend all ingredients and place in freezer.
Remove from freezer approximately 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix well and fold in 1/3 cup cream, whipped.
Delicious over fruit.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1-quart cup, mix sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir in soda.
Spread on buttered pan and cool.

title: chewy noels(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in an 8-inch square pan over low heat.
Take off stove.
Beat eggs.
Combine sugar, flour, soda and nuts and stir into beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture over butter.
Do not stir!
Bake 25 minutes.
Turn out of pan onto rack.
Cut into squares and dust with powdered sugar.

title: peppermint pinwheels christmas cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Mix flour and salt; blend in thoroughly.
Divide dough in half.
Blend red food coloring into one-half.
Chill dough until firm.
On lightly floured cloth covered board, roll dough.
Roll double layer of dough gently until 3/16-inch thick.
Roll up tightly as for jelly roll.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Slice 1/8-inch thick. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 9 minutes or until lightly browned.
While still warm, brush with egg white glaze and sprinkle with mixture of candy and sugar.

title: hamburger skillet
directions: Using electric skillet, press 3/4 ground beef in bottom of skillet. Then add cabbage, carrots, mushroom soup, onion and cheese. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour; stir in juice.
Add cheese and pineapple, mixing well.
Spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs; mix well.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
This is good as a side dish for meat, especially ham.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar again while warm.
(Dough may be colored if desired.)

title: pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Mix well.
If batter becomes too thick, more milk can be added.
Fry in lightly greased skillet.
Makes about 4 (6-inch) pancakes.

title: muddy buddies or "puppy chow"
directions: Place cereals into a large bowl and set aside.
In a 1-quart microwave bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute intervals.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are coated.
Pour cereal mixture into a resealable plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: perfect play dough
directions: You will also need a medium pot, resealable bag or airtight container, wooden spoon and plastic scraper.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain fat.
Remove to absorbent paper. Measure 2 tablespoons of fat into frying pan and coo k onions and cayenne into the mushroom soup.
In a deep casserole dish, alternate layers of drained string beans, crumbled bacon, mushroom soup with onions (do not add water).
Sprinkle almonds and cracker crumbs on top.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange sliced potatoes and 1 teaspoon onion in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and parsley.
Combine ground beef, milk, crackers, ketchup, remaining onion and seasonings.
Spread over sliced potatoes. Decorate with additional ketchup, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar in bowl until light and fluffy. Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture into greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: peaches & cream cheesecake
directions: *(Peaches can be chopped in smaller pieces.)

title: pineapple apple dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
If you make 1/2 of this recipe use an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Bake half the batter for 15 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Mix caramels, butter and milk; melt.
Pour over baked, cooled cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stir-fried shrimp and vegetables
directions: Use sharp knife to thinly slice carrots and mushrooms.
Shell and devein shrimp.
Halve shrimp lengthwise.
Blend chicken broth into cornstarch; stir in soy sauce and set aside.
Preheat wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add oil for 30 seconds.
Add cauliflower and carrots; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add bok choy, pea pods, mushrooms and bean sprouts; stir-fry 2 minutes more, or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables to bowl. Add shrimp to wok or skillet; stir-fry 7 to 8 minutes.
Push shrimp away from center.
Stir in chicken broth mixture; cook until thick and bubbly.

title: angel delight
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces in a deep large bowl.
Mix cheese and milk.
Pour over cake.
Top with Cool Whip; top with pie filling.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in rice and sprinkle with salt. Top with chicken pieces.
Dilute canned soup with water and pour over chicken.
Top with onion soup mix.
Seal with foil and bake at 325° about 2 hours.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: Place 1 marshmallow on 1 graham cracker.
Place in microwave for 15 to 30 seconds until marshmallow expands.
Spread marshmallow over cracker.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Cook broccoli and rice according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients; put in baking dish.
Shred some Cheddar cheese and sprinkle on top (optional).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Toss pecans with mixture of oil and Worcestershire sauce. Roast in a shallow baking pan at 275° for 30 minutes, stirring every five minutes. Drain pecans on paper towel and sprinkle with salt.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil whole chicken until it's falling apart. Remove skin and bone from chicken. In a large bowl, mix shredded chicken, 2 cans of enchilada sauce, diced onion and 2 cups of cheese. Pour a small amount of chicken broth in the bottom of 2 casserole dishes. Roll chicken mixture in tortillas. Pour the remaining 2 cans of enchilada sauce over the rolled enchiladas and spread the remaining cheese over the top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for
about 30 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Blend all ingredients except chocolate stars.
Make into small balls (will make about 6 dozen).
Roll in white sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and press chocolate stars or kisses into center.
Return to oven and bake for 3 minutes more. These freeze well.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown the hamburg.
Add water and bay leaves plus bouillon. Cover and heat to boiling.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Turn heat to low and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: creamy strawberry pie
directions: Prepare pie crust as directed. Prepare gelatin as directed using 3/4 cup hot water, 3/4 cup cold water and lemon juice. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white. Gently stir in whipped topping and strawberries. Spoon into shell. Chill for 3 hours. Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: cherry cheesecake pudding
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into dishes or serving bowl.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix
together
all ingredients.
Bake at
350°	for
30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Rub top with a
stick of butter (margarine) while bread is still hot.
Serve warm.

title: cathy's smothered meatballs and onions
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Roll ground beef into medium size balls. Roll in flour and place in skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Drain oil and pour enough water just to the top of meatballs.
Slice onions over top of meatballs and cook until tender.

title: black-eyed pea pie
directions: Beat peas and butter in bowl.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Pour into crust.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown onion and ground chuck; drain off excess fat.
Mix with other ingredients and bake at 400 degrees for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: pizza buns
directions: Brown ground meat, onions and garlic.
Add rest of ingredients, except Mozzarella.
Spread mixture on split English muffins and sprinkle grated Mozzarella over the top.
Broil until brown.
Quick and easy, plus children love these!

title: easy cake(based on 1-2-3-4 recipe)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, then other ingredients. Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: fettucini
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Cook until lightly browned. Add 1 cup cream and cook until slightly thickened.
Cook and drain noodles.
Add noodles and 1/2 cup grated cheese to sauce; mix well.
Add 1/4 cup more cream.
Stir and toss over the heat.
Add the rest of the cheese and cream; toss well.
Serve immediately. Goes great with garlic bread and salad!

title: yummy pepper steak with rice
directions: As
the
rice cooks, pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into
strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika.	Brown meat in butter; add garlic.
Pour 2 cups broth over meat; add onions. Cover and let cook until meat is tender.
Cut green peppers in strips.
Cut 2
large tomatoes in eighths.
Add cornstarch to 1/4
cup
and 1/4
cup
of
soy sauce.
Dissolve and put into skillet to thicken.
Add pepper and tomato pieces.
Cook until pepper is tender (not
falling apart).
Spread over platter of rice. Garnish with chopped
ground onion bits.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Lay 1/3 of crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Lay in 1/3 more of crackers and add rest of pudding.
Lay rest of crackers over top.
Top with chocolate sauce and refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate and margarine. Add rest of ingredients.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in vanilla and next three ingredients.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: milk chocolate peanut buttery cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, sugar, milk, butter and vanilla in a large bowl until creamy.
Add egg, combine flour, soda and salt.
Add slowly to other mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies; 12 to 14 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over shredded cabbage.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Butter a shallow baking dish 12 x 8-inch.
Slice potatoes in thick slices, arrange one layer, then top with cranberry sauce, brown sugar, butter and crumbs; repeat until dish is filled.
Be sure sweet potatoes and crumbs make the top layer and add a little more butter on top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about half an hour--no more.
Serves 8 generously.
This is delicious with ham, pork, turkey or chicken.

title: asparagus with zest
directions: Snap off the tough ends of the asparagus; peel the stalks. Steam the stalks in a small amount of water in a saucepan until tender-crisp.
Refresh in ice water and drain.
Combine the lemon zest, anchovy paste and lemon juice in a bowl; mix well.
Place the asparagus in a serving bowl.
Spoon the lemon rind relish over the asparagus; garnish lightly with the shaved Parmesan cheese.
A tasty side dish for spring and summer entertaining.
For a memorable presentation, tie beautiful bows around bundles of asparagus, using scallions or leeks which have been softened in boiling water.

title: creamy ranch potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in quarters.
Layer into bottom of 9X9 greased pan.
In bowl, mix sour cream, ranch dressing and soup.
Salt and pepper potatoes to taste and mix with soup mixture until well coated.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs and bake at 300 degrees for 3 1/2
hours.
Can be made a day ahead, they keep great.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in small amount of oil; add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 60 minutes.
Drain pineapple, reserving the juice.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, pineapple chunks, green pepper and onions.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over rice. If using leftover pork, it only takes about 10 to 15 minutes to warm through.

title: onion casserole
directions: Put onions in well-greased
casserole dish.
Cover with mushroom soup and sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for
hour or until onions are tender.

title: sausage and bean soup
directions: In 4-quart nonstick pot, heat the oil.
Add pepper and onion and cook until tender, not soft.
Stir frequently, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not brown.
Brown sausage and drain.
Also drain the liquid from both the kidney and Northern beans.
Add the beans and crushed tomatoes to the sausage.
Fill the empty tomato can 1/2 full of water.
Add to soup.
Dissolve the chicken bouillon in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add to soup.
Stir well.
Simmer on low 1 hour. Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, 1 hour.
Sprinkle fresh green parsley.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.

title: corn dog mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add egg and enough water to make medium batter.
Mix well; let stand 15 minutes.
Put stick in wieners; roll in mix.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: snack mix
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in large pan.
After melted, remove from heat.
Coat Rice Chex with mixture.
Shake Rice Chex with confectioners sugar.

title: cranberry cooler
directions: Mix together cranberry juice and lemonade concentrate.
Add Ginger-Ale or Lemon-lime soda.
Pour over ice in tall glasses. Garnish with slices of lime.

title: hearty chili
directions: Place ground beef and onion in Dutch oven. Cook and stir over medium heat, 8 to 10 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, breaking beef into small crumbles. Drain, if necessary. Drain and rinse black beans. Add black beans, chili beans, tomatoes, soup and chili powder to meat mixture in Dutch oven. Bring to a boil; reduce heat, and simmer covered, over low heat 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: snow peas with garlic dip
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with snow peas.
Yield:
1 cup.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Mix yeast mixture with buttermilk, sugar and salt. Set aside. Sift flour, baking powder and soda together. Cut in shortening. Add liquid mixture. Mix lightly. Knead, roll, cut and bake. Dough may be refrigerated 4 to 5 days and used as needed. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Can also be cut into biscuits and frozen on a cookie sheet until firm and then transferred to a freezer bag. Makes about 50 biscuits.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in saucepan.
Blend in milk and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until mixture boils; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve warm.
Yields 2 cups.

title: german rabbit recipe
directions: Cut up rabbit and marinate in red wine, pickling spices, salt, diced carrots, celery, onion and 1 cup water for 2 or 3 days. Dry rabbit on paper towel; coat with flour, salt and pepper. Brown in bacon fat.
Add garlic while frying.
Strain marinade for gravy.
Add gravy to meat and simmer for 3/4 hour.
Add chopped mushrooms and continue cooking 15 minutes, or until meat is done.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Brown meat with onion, garlic and mushrooms in a large pan.
Add zucchini, spinach and sun-dried tomatoes, along with some salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer over medium heat, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes, then add pasta sauce, tomato paste, water and oregano.
Reduce to low-medium heat and simmer about five minutes, stirring often.
Sauce should be watery.
Add cottage cheese and remove from heat.

title: barbecue sauce (hot dogs)
directions: Mix together and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add hot dogs until cooked and serve.

title: gingerbread topping
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook and stir until thickened. Add nutmeg and vanilla.
Spoon over gingerbread just before serving.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix corn syrup, vinegar, margarine, sugar, salt and pepper together.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: breakfast
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Place bread in bottom of 5 x 7-inch or 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Add drained sausage and layer of grated cheese.
Mix eggs and remaining ingredients and pour over meat mixture.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried peach pieces
directions: Place peaches in bowl; sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over peaches and set aside for about 1 hour.
Place peaches, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar in saucepan.
Slowly cook peaches down to pie filling consistency.
If necessary, add 1 or 2 tablespoons cornstarch to thicken.
Place 3 cups flour into a mixing bowl; cut in shortening with a fork.
Slowly add 1 1/2 cups cold water; roll out on floured board.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick the size of saucer. Spoon 3 or 4 tablespoons pie filling into each round.
Fold over and flute edges with a fork.
Heat vegetable oil in electric skillet between 300° to 325°.
Fry pies until golden brown on both sides.

title: mexican dip
directions: Make layers in order of ingredients. Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: yum yum cake with icing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan on 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cake mix with cinnamon.
Add pie filling and eggs.
Stir until combined.
Pour batter into lightly greased and floured Bundt cake pan (or angel food cake pan).
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool thoroughly.
Sift confectioners sugar lightly over cake.

title: german stuffed cabbage
directions: Steam cabbage until leaves are easily removed.
