Mix ground beef, bread crumbs and onions with salt and pepper. Set aside. Peel leaves and line inside of steamer basket with the leaves, bottom and sides.
Put thin layer of meat mixture on bottom. Cover with thick layer of leaves.
Add meat and cabbage leaves until all is used up.
Put a little water in bottom of steamer. Add the basket and cover.
Boil for about 2 hours.
Pull out steamer basket and flip stuffed cabbage onto a plate.
Slice as if slicing a cake.
Serve with Hollandaise Sauce and mashed potatoes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; slowly stir in corn oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours at 300°.

title: fish cakes
directions: Place fish in a medium bowl; use fork to break up and mix. Add meal; then blend in egg, well.
Use seasonings and add chopped onion, mixing well.
Roll in cracker crumbs or meal by tablespoon to make flat cakes.
Brown in oil (Crisco, Puritan or olive oil).

title: appetizers - pizza dip
directions: Whip together cream cheese, sour cream and spices. Spread in oven-safe pie plate. Cover with pizza sauce. Sprinkle with onions, peppers and pepperoni. Cover with shredded Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted. Serve with crackers.

title: mexican bites
directions: Place chips on baking sheet. Top each with onions, chilis, cheese and a little smokie! Heat until cheese melts. Serve warm.

title: secret salad dressing
directions: Mix the ingredients together and chill at least 8 hours before using (very important!!!).

title: finger lickin' good pork chops
directions: Batter pork chops with flour, quick brown pork chops on both sides in skillet.
Place browned pork chops in slow cooker and pour soup
on top.
Cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: hawaiian pineapple pie
directions: Combine eggs
and
corn syrup;
beat until well blended. Stir in other
ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into pie shells and bake at 350°
for about 30 minutes or until pastry is brown and filling is firm.

title: bean and cornbread casserole
directions: Coat a large, no-stick skillet with vegetable cooking spray. Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir in kidney beans and next 7 ingredients (drain beans before adding).
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with Pam.
Set aside.

title: sliced potato bake
directions: Peel potatoes and slice fairly thin.
Mix oil, Parmesan cheese, paprika, salt and pepper in a mixing cup.
Place potato slices in a baking dish, overlapping slices in rows.
Pour oil mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: chicken marinade marie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate chicken in sauce for 14 hours. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Turn after 1/2 hour.
Recipe makes enough for approximately 3 pound cut up chicken.

title: apricot cake
directions: Blend top 5 ingredients until moist.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pre-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Let stand in pan for 15 minutes.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes until it is at room temperature.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all together and cook 20 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook sugar, butter, dates until mixture melts. Stir in cereal and nuts. Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar in softened butter.
Add flour and beaten eggs. Stir in buttermilk.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Reserve a few bread crumbs for topping. After mixing all ingredients together and putting in casserole dish, top with the reserved bread crumbs and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: deviled ham cornucopias
directions: Cut bread into 20 rounds.
Flatten with rolling pin; spread both sides of bread with mayonnaise.
Roll into cornucopias shape and fasten with toothpicks.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes (lightly brown).
Remove toothpick.

title: great guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until blended.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: venison or elk finger steaks
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch wide strips and pound lightly with tenderizing hammer.
Dip strips of mixture in half soy sauce and half Worcestershire sauce.
Roll in flour and fry in butter or bacon fat.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt. Mix well. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Toss apples with water and lemon juice. Spoon into casserole and sprinkle with flour mixture. Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate in shallow baking dish, covered, overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in a bowl.
Add eggs, bananas, biscuit mix and nuts.
Beat well.

title: apple fritters
directions: Blend all dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg.
Mix thoroughly. Dip apple slices in batter for complete coating and fry in 370° deep oil for 3 minutes.
Serve with syrups and jellies.

title: cheese and shrimp dip spread
directions: Put cheese
on	platter.
Pour	1/2
of sauce over all. Pour shrimp over sauce.	Pour rest of sauce over all.

title: chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk in the top of a double boiler. Place over hot water and stir until mixture melts. Add chocolate bar; stir until melted and smooth. Cool to room temperature.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well.
Melt oleo in saucepan, pour in egg mixture and chopped dates.
Stir and cook until mixture thickens and turns dark brown (3 to 5 minutes after mixture boils).
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat, add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Cool slightly.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Combine butter, flour, powdered sugar, nuts and place on bottom of 9x13 pan. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 cool whip and place on top of crust.
Mix pudding and milk and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining half of cool whip and sprinkle with pecans.

title: applesauce jello salad
directions: Heat 7-Up with red hots until dissolved.
Pour over Jell-O; mix well and let cool.
Add applesauce and refrigerate until firm.

title: wine sauerkraut
directions: Rinse sauerkraut once before cooking with tap water.
Combine with Pignuckles in pot big enough that both are covered with fresh water.
Then cook for 1 hour until Pignuckles are done.
One-half hour before sauerkraut is done, put potatoes on stove and cook. After 1 hour, take Pignuckles out; combine 1 tablespoon flour with water and stir until smooth.
Spoon under sauerkraut, wine and Pignuckles.
Let simmer for another 10 minutes.
Potatoes should be done by now.
Discard water; serve and enjoy!

title: dang good pie (pineapple)
directions: Mix all ingredients (1 egg at a time).
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until center is solid.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip or serve plain.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together squash, carrot, onion, sour cream, soup and margarine in a casserole dish.
Top with the prepared Stove Top stuffing and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Mix cocoa with boiling water; set aside to cool.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
In dry ingredients, make a well and add in order:
Wesson oil, egg yolks, cooled cocoa mixture and vanilla.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon in large bowl.
Stir in peaches and lemon juice.
Turn into pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust.
Slit, seal and flute covered edge of crust with foil to prevent overbrowning.
Remove last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake at 425° about 45 minutes.

title: low fat manicotti
directions: Heat a frying pan.
Add the olive oil, onions, garlic, celery and peppers.
Saute until the whites of the onions turn clear.
Add ground turkey.
Cook until the turkey is done.
Drain well.
Add approximately 1/3 cup of the wine into the pan.
Simmer until the wine is reduced by half.
Drain well again.
The wine will cut the olive oil and some of the fat of the turkey and add taste.
Mix meat mixture with thawed and drained spinach.
Put tofu in a blender and blend until smooth.
Stir into mixture.
Stir in rest of the ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stuff manicotti tubes with the mixture.
Place stuffed tubes in a glass roasting dish. Pour fat free commercial (Healthy Choice is good) or homemade spaghetti sauce.
It must cover the tubes.
Bake covered for 1 hour.
Serve tubes with low-fat grated Romano cheese.

title: baked chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients and 1 cup cheese in a large bowl until well blended. Wrap tortillas in heavy-duty plastic wrap; heat in microwave according to package directions. Spoon about 1/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each warm tortilla; roll up. Place in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cook diced tomatoes, tomato sauce and cream in a 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring often, 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Pour tomato mixture evenly over tortillas, spreading to ends of tortillas; sprinkle with remaining 2 cups cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and tomato mixture is bubbly. Serve with desired topping of sour cream and shredded lettuce.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container; cover and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
(A quick breakfast on the run.)

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Use a toothpick.
If comes out clean, is done.
Takes about 35 minutes in preheated oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute butter and onion; stir in flour and salt.
Add water and cook until thick.
Add cheese; stir until blended.
Combine with broccoli; blend in beaten egg and pour in greased baking dish. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: lean chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In pot, over low heat, melt spread.
Add sugar and blend well.
Remove from heat, stir in cocoa and vanilla.
Add egg substitute and stir to blend.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 25 minutes or until edges begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan.
Sprinkle top of brownies with powdered sugar.
Contains 16 squares, 3 g fat and 100 calories each.

title: magic easter eggs
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and salt in medium mixing bowl; blend until smooth.
Add sugar gradually, blending well after each addition.
Blend until mixture is very stiff.
Turn onto clean board and knead in all remaining sugar carefully.
Mixture should be smooth and not sticky.
Cut mixture into desired number of pieces.
Mold each piece into shape with palm of hands.
Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheet and chill for several hours or overnight.
Coconut eggs may be made by kneading in 3 cups flaked coconut
after all sugar has been kneaded into fondant.
Almond eggs may be made by substituting 1 teaspoon almond extract.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. Add 1/3 cup of mix to each 8 ounce cup of hot water.

title: sorghum pie
directions: Beat eggs and rest of ingredients in order given.
Turn in partially baked pie shell and bake at 425° until just firm.
Do not over cook.

title: pecan-raisin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar, adding sugar slowly, creaming until fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add the spices, raisins, vanilla extract and pecans.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Easy and tasty.
Bon Appetit!

title: arthur treachers' fish coating
directions: Put fish fillets in buttermilk and a slice of lemon. Refrigerate for 2 hours. Remove fish from the buttermilk and discard lemon. Combine pancake mix and club soda to consistency of buttermilk. Heat oil in skillet until hot. Dip fish in batter; let excess drop off. Fry fish 4 minutes on each side. Drain on paper towels and keep warm until eating!

title: homemade irish cream liquor
directions: In a blender container combine all ingredients until smooth. Serve over ice if desired.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator up to one month.
Stir before serving.

title: chili ii
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add ground beef and cook; drain off the fat.
In a bowl mix together sweet pickle juice (optional), salt and pepper, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and chili beans.
Pour sauce in pot with ground beef and simmer for 30 minutes.
May need to add water to make it thinner.

title: quick and easy cheese balls
directions: Ingredient proportions depend on how many you want to make.

title: butternut balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt, vanilla and flour, mixing well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Roll each in powdered sugar while warm.
Yield: 3 dozen balls.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a greased baking dish.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, shortening, sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to mix.
Add milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: buttery walnut stuffing
directions: Add enough turkey or chicken broth to moisten.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Turn into large baking pan and bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: strawberry-nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (8 1/2 or 9-inch) cake pans.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost layers.

title: mushroom-stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Cook zucchini shells in boiling salt water for 4 minutes. Drain; arrange shells in greased baking dish.
Soak bread in milk for 3 minutes.
Squeeze out excess milk; set aside bread.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Add chopped zucchini flesh; season well.
Cook for 6 minutes over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and garlic; season and cook 7 minutes.
Mix in bread, then add cooked onion.
Mix again; cook 3 minutes.
Divide mixture between zucchini; sprinkle with cheese.
Cook for 18 minutes in oven.

title: stuffed potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, margarine, chives and garlic.
Beat together.
Spoon into buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover dish with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Dish may be prepared and kept in refrigerator overnight.)
Makes 12 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place rolls on cookie sheet, pressing to cover pan.
Bake until light brown.
Spread mayo mix on baked dough.
Put veggies on top.
Cover with shredded Cheddar.

title: meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, place all of your meat, then all the ingredients that follow.
Mix with your clean hands.
Mix very well, then take about 1/4 to 1/3 cup of the mixture in hand and roll until a ball forms.
You can either lightly fry the meatballs in olive oil, then put them in your spaghetti sauce, or you can put them in your sauce raw and let them simmer until they are cooked.
Either way, they are good.
Skim off the fat from your spaghetti sauce if you choose to cook them right in the sauce.

title: cranberry nut muffins
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, orange juice, eggs and berries.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir wet mixture into dry ingredients.
Fill 12 greased or paper-lined muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: deviled eggs in creamed sauce(easter breakfast)
directions: Remove yolks from eggs and mix with remaining ingredients. Fill egg cavities with mixture and place eggs in a single layer in shallow baking dish. Pour sauce over top of eggs.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, peanut butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add baking soda and flour (together).
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoonful on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie. Yields about 4 1/2 dozen (if you don't eat too much of the batter!).

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute chopped green onion with tops and chopped green pepper in butter or margarine.
Mix all together except buttered crumbs.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole or individual shells.
Sprinkle top with 2 cups buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seminary pudding
directions: Mix oleo, flour, brown sugar, almonds and coconut.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°, stirring often, to brown evenly (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Combine milk, vanilla pudding, coconut cream pudding and Cool Whip.
Layer in deep bowl starting with first mixture.
Save some of the first mixture to sprinkle on top.

title: self-rising beer bread
directions: Grease 1 loaf pan.
Set aside.
Mix together flour, sugar and beer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great bread to serve with chili or stews.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Then mix the next 3 ingredients.
It will make a batter.
Pour over the first ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: golden broccoli soup
directions: In 3-quart microwave, combine broccoli, carrot, onion and water.
Cover with lid. Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Grease 2 to 3 quart casserole dish.
Mix together last 5 ingredients.

title: cherry waldorf gelatin(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: In bowl, pour boiling water over gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and ReaLemon brand; chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into lightly oiled 6-cup mold or 9-inch square pan.
Chill until set, 4 to 6 hours.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish as desired.

title: christmas applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves together.
Mix applesauce with baking soda in small bowl.

title: spicy pintos and sausage
directions: Rinse beans and cover with cold water.
Soak overnight. Drain.
Add cold water to beans until water level is about 4-inches above beans.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Put flour, sugar and soda in sifter.
In bowl, pour in fruit cocktail, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well with spoon.
Pour into large greased oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Start topping 10 minutes before cake is done.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Cook small beets until tender.
Cold dip and skip off skins. Cover with pickle syrup and simmer 15 minutes.
Seal in clean jars.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook
zucchini
in
a little boiling water, add 1/2 teaspoon salt to water.
Do not overcook; drain.
Cook carrots and onions in
4 tablespoons oleo until tender.
Remove from heat, stir in
cups dressing,
soup,
sour
cream and cheese. Gently
stir in
zucchini.
Turn in casserole.
Melt remaining oleo and add to remaining Pepperidge Farm dressing, toss gently and top
the casserole
with
this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Cook a recipe of rice a day ahead of time.
One cup dry rice to 2 cups water.
It is better if it has dried out, but it can be made early and cooled.
Brown diced bacon (crisp) in a skillet.
Do not pour off the drippings.
Push bacon to side and turn down heat. Next, break in 3 or 4 whole eggs and scramble in the bacon drippings.
Add the rice and 3 or 4 cut up green onion tops and all.
Add soy sauce until it is as brown as desired.
Stir and cook on low heat 15 to 20 minutes, then serve.

title: oreo cookie ice cream dessert
directions: Mix 1 stick butter and cookies. Spread in 9 x 13 cake pan. (Reserve some cookies for the top of the dessert.) Freeze overnight. Spread the ice cream over cookie mixture and freeze overnight.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cocoa together.
Mix Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, then add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately.
Add vinegar and food coloring.
Frost cake with your favorite white frosting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion according to directions on squash package, omitting salt.
Drain well, pressing between paper towels to remove excess liquid.
Combine squash mixture, mayonnaise and next 4 ingredients in a lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef, draining fat.
Add sour cream, beans, approximately 4 ounces cheese and picante sauce to your taste. Heat on stove until hot.
Put in tortilla shells, rolling as burritos.
Top with shredded cheese and put in oven or microwave and heat until cheese melts.

title: autumn glory apple-cranberry pie(8 servings)
directions: Prepare the pastry; divide into 2 portions.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out one portion of pastry.
Fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Trim pastry 1/2 inch beyond edge of pie plate. Roll out remaining pastry for top crust; cover and set aside.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut veggies into small pieces.
Ham should be cut very small also.
Mix all ingredients together and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy creamy icing(for gingerbread boys)
directions: Blend sugar, salt and vanilla. Add water.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all together. Fry like potato pancakes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: alaska cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, milk and salt. Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, margarine and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop into wax paper and refrigerate 5 minutes.

title: golden artichoke salad
directions: Mix liquid out of artichokes with desired amount of mayonnaise.
Blend in 1/2 to 1 teaspoon curry powder.
Toss all ingredients.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, oats, cinnamon and butter together. Pat half of mixture into large, greased pie pan.
Pour in apples. Cook 1 cup sugar, the cornstarch and water until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Pour over apples and cover with remainder of crumb mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: endive salad
directions: Wash endive and cut in bite size pieces. Drain and place in large bowl. Brown bacon in skillet and add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Cut 2 hard-boiled eggs fine and blend with endive. Add minced onion, then pour hot vinegar syrup over endive mix. Slice 2 hard-cooked eggs to garnish the top and serve the salad in small bowls.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift the flour, soda, sugar and salt.
Bring oleo, water, shortening and cocoa to a boil; add to the flour mixture.
Beat eggs, cinnamon, buttermilk and vanilla together; add to all the other ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 12 x 17 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, cooking
oil and pudding mix together. Add water and poppy seed.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool
in
pans
10 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil (4 minutes on High in the microwave).
Then cook for 10 to 12 minutes on High, stopping to stir every minute.
Watch very carefully after 8 minutes!
Test for doneness of hard candy by dropping a small dollop into cold water.
Sugar mixture will be golden brown when done.

Pour sugar mixture onto aluminum foil and immediately cover with the chopped pecans and then Hershey's chocolate squares. When cooled, break into pieces and store in an airtight container. Makes an excellent Christmas gift!

title: spicy oven fries
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Peel potatoes and cut lengthwise into strips, about 1/2-inch thick.
Spread in a single layer in 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with oil, turning to coat evenly. Combine salt, oregano, onion salt, pepper, chili powder and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle half of spice mixture over potatoes. Bake 12 minutes.
Turn potatoes and sprinkle with remaining spice and cheese mixture.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes longer.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: dressing
directions: Cook hen until	done,
about
1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cook 2 pans corn bread	and
let cool.	Put cut up chicken in a large roaster pan. (I
always
save some of the white breast meat to put in giblet
gravy.)
Crumble
corn bread over meat. Cut up onion and celery.
Beat 3 eggs with mixer until frothy and add to dressing. Season
with
sage, salt and pepper.
Pour broth from hen
over dressing.
Stir well. Add enough broth to stay juicy even after being cooked.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Pull chicken from bone. Place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add broccoli.
Mix together cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Spread over top of chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle stuffing over top.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: coconut candy
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut in a saucepan and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to 245° on a candy thermometer or firm ball stage.
Remove from heat and add coconut.
Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet.
Shape into peaked mounds.
Sweet and chewy.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Mix chicken and soup.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake until crust is brown at 350°.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Place in blender or processor; blend.
Heat and top with chives.

title: crispy polynesian butterscotch cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Beat butter, oil, sugars, egg and vanilla until creamy. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels, oats, crushed cereal, coconut and nuts. Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes or until edges are crisp but centers are still slightly soft. Let stand 2 minutes; remove to wire racks. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: flowerpot (dirt) dessert
directions: Soften	margarine and cream cheese at room temperature. Grind cookies
in
blender and set aside.
Cream together the butter, cream
cheese and powdered sugar. Add milk to pudding mix and
mix together.	Fold
in
Cool Whip.
Layer in pot or bowl,
cookies on	the
bottom, cream, cookies, cream and top with cookies.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain and mash salmon, reserving liquid.
Combine salmon with bread crumbs, egg whites, onion, parsley, lemon juice and pepper; mix well.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons of reserved liquid, if necessary, for desired consistency.
Shape into patties.
Brown in skillet with oil over medium heat.

title: spicy peach bread
directions: Blend first 10 ingredients at low speed until blended.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350° in bread pan or square pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Combine chicken, soup and sour cream and put in a greased 8 x 8-inch dish.
Crush crackers fine and add melted butter, mix thoroughly.
Put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix or toss in a plastic bag just before serving.
Add Catalina dressing and toss again in serving bowl.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until bubbles.
Simmer and remove
from heat.	Stir in 3 tablespoons of butter.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice and dash of salt.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve with wild rice and steamed broccoli.
Serves 4.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; put into jars, adding a few dill stalks and 1 or 2 garlic buttons.

title: turkey breast
directions: Thaw breast (about half).
Salt and pepper.
Place in foil-lined baking dish, enough foil to wrap breast good.
Pour water around breast, pour sauce over breast.
Wrap tightly with foil.
Bake about 6 hours at 300°.

title: bell pepper bake
directions: Mix together onion, crackers, egg, water, 2 teaspoons salt and 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Cut the top of bell peppers and take the seeds out.
Put meat inside.
Mix garlic powder, tomato soup, water, 3 teaspoons of salt and 1 teaspoon of sugar to make sauce. Pour everything together.
Put bell pepper and sauce into baking pan.
Put in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy lentil salad
directions: Bring a saucepan of lightly salted water to a boil and add the lentils.
Reduce the heat and simmer until crisp-tender, about 30 minutes.
Drain the lentils; rinse them under cold water and pat dry.
Place them in a salad bowl and add all the remaining ingredients.
Toss well to combine.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours (to develop the flavors) before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 portions.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions.
Add frozen strawberries. Add sliced bananas and crushed pineapple.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a glass serving dish.
Refrigerate about 1 hour; then add sour cream and remaining mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fry broccoli and onion until tender.
Add chicken soup and heat slowly for 10 minutes.
Stir in Cheez Whiz, rice and milk. Pour in baking dish.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: butter buds
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Add eggs, then rest of ingredients.
Roll dough into marble size balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press with fork.
Place a cherry half on each one. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls and place in baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Cut avocados in half. Take pit out. Mash with fork coarsely. Stir in all other ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: divinity
directions: Lightly toast two or more cups pecans and chop.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Cook water, Karo syrup and sugar until it spins a thread.
Pour half of mixture over stiffly beaten eggs.
Continue cooking until it spins a long thread.
Pour the rest in and beat.
Stir in pecans and vanilla. Drop by spoonful onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: jello punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Freeze and stir every 3 hours until it starts to set. Does not freeze real solid.
Add 2 quarts ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 40.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: peach jelly
directions: *Boil peelings and pits left from making Peach Jam in 5 cups of water for 10 minutes to make 4 cups juice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and mix well. Pour apples into casserole dish and top with dry crumb mixture. Bake until apples are tender, about 30 minutes at 250°.

title: deviled brussels sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts according to package directions; drain well.
Melt margarine in small saucepan; add all remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Pour over Brussels sprouts. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot water.
Remove from heat; stir in brown sugar.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Blend in eggs, softened oleo and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spread in a greased, lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.
Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: vegetable soup(no meat; low-fat)
directions: Peel and chop raw vegetables.
Add frozen and/or canned from package or can.
Add water to desired consistency. The lentils add protein and make the broth brown and rich, giving the soup a "meaty" flavor.
Amounts of vegetables may vary according to what leftovers are on hand.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well.
Add flour and dry ingredients and then the water.
Beat until smooth; add berries.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot tea beverage
directions: Bring water to just under a boil.
Add tea bags; let steep. Heat juice.
Put all in bowl (wassail) or pitcher, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Serve with cinnamon stick in cup (optional).

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container and cook until skins of tomatoes begin to break.
Pack tomatoes into 10 sterilized hot quart jars or 20 pint jars.
Seal.

title: romany steak
directions: Fry bacon, cut into small pieces, in a skillet until fat is rendered but bacon is not crisp.
Add round steak and brown on both sides.
Add soup, undiluted, cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Turn off heat, add egg and stir vigorously.
Serve immediately on hot toast.

title: chicken-spinach-mushroom quiche
directions: Place pie shell in Pyrex pie plate.
Beat one egg and brush bottom of pie shell.
Cook spinach as directed.
Drain.
Beat other 4 eggs; add milk, salt, Tabasco sauce, mushrooms, drained spinach, onions, celery and bell pepper.
Toss together chicken, cheese and flour.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour into pie crust. Bake in a preheated 400° oven on a cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes or until center puffs up slightly, or a knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes!!!!

title: cheesy brats and beer
directions: Brown brats.
Add onion and beer and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Mix margarine and onion salt and spread on buns.
Take brats; slit middles.
Place on broiler pan and fill slits with cheese.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 2 minutes.
Remove.
Place brats on buns.
Sprinkle with some of the drained onion and crumbled bacon.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, cream butter; add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add poppy seed, lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat at high speed for two minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool before glazing.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain liquid from all vegetables.
Mix all vegetables.
Mix dressing and pour over vegetables.
Mix well and allow to set overnight in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: betty's spareribs
directions: Season both sides of meat with salt, pepper and garlic powder (optional).
Lay one slab in bottom of Nesco or roasting pan with cover.
Put pitted prunes and onion and about 2 tablespoons water on spareribs and cover with other slab.
Bake covered at 350° about one hour.
Add peeled fresh potato chunks and more onion wedges.
Stir to get covered with pan juice.
Continue baking until done, ribs will be brown.

title: apple squares cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Add vanilla and beat well.
Stir in pineapple and coconut.

title: funsten pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat eggs slightly in a 2-quart bowl. Stir in sugar, corn syrup and melted butter or margarine.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. (You may use 5 eggs and double the recipe for 2 pies.)

title: super coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored and creamy.
Add sugar slowly. Add oil and beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Add dry ingredients and beat 1 minute.
Spread 1/2 mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour on pie filling.
Top with rest of dough.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup brown sugar and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir jello and water until jello is dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce until mixed well.
Stir in pineapple; add nuts.
Chill until set.

title: cranberry spike
directions: Combine chilled juices.
Serve over ice cubes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Pour hot syrup slowly over beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Cut celery into small pieces.
Cook celery, onion and pimento in small saucepan for 15 minutes.
While mixture simmers, wash eggplant and cut and slice into 1/4-inch slices or cubes.
In a saucepan, heat small amount salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add eggplant.
Cover and heat to boiling; cook 5 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Add onion, celery and pimento, then add salt, pepper, sage, oleo, bread crumbs and cheese.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes.
Oven temperature:

title: peanut salad
directions: Put peanut butter, potato, onion and seasoning in bowl.
Beat well together; form into small balls.
Mount each on slice of beetroot or tomato.
Arrange lettuce leaves in bowl and place mounted peanut balls on them.
Serve salad dressing separately and a dish of grated cheese or of thinly sliced chopped ham.
(GE)

title: ann mathney's lasagna
directions: Cook meat with spaghetti sauce mix.
Add bell pepper, onion, tomato sauce and oregano.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese with 1 teaspoon pepper.
Layer meat, noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat 3 times.
Bake at 350°
until hot and bubbly.

title: apple squares
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add creamed mixture with apples and nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for forty minutes.
Peel and chop apples.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger meat with onion and green pepper.
Chop the meat up as it is cooking.
When done, drain the grease off.
Use 1 large can of pork and beans; add to hamburger mixture.
Add ketchup and mustard; mix well.
Put in baking dish.
Lay bacon across top.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: creamy tuna dip
directions: Stir milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, into cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, green onions, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Blend well.
Stir in tuna.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Garnish with paprika and parsley.

title: peanut butter chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, stir together melted butter, graham cracker crumbs, cocoa and 1/3 cup sugar; press evenly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese and remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar until combined. Stir in peanut butter chips; pour over prepared crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until slightly puffed and center is set except for 4-inch circle in center; remove from oven.
Cool 30 minutes. Loosen cheese cake from rim of pan.
Cool to room temperature. Using the tip of spoon, drizzle Chocolate Drizzle across top of cheesecake.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Remove rim of pan.
Cover and refrigerate leftovers.

title: pound cake
directions: Margarine and Crisco should be room temperature. Combine sugar, margarine and Crisco until creamy. Add eggs 1 at a time. Add cake flour, baking powder and buttermilk. Beat mixture until fluffy. Pour into a greased tube cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease
and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine
all	ingredients
in
a large bowl and mix well. Transfer
to
prepared
pan.
Bake	until top is golden brown and split slightly (1 hour and 20 minutes).
Serve warm. Makes 1 loaf. Do not double recipe!

title: beef with onions
directions: Combine beef, salt, egg white and cornstarch.
Mix well with hands.
Heat oil in wok.
Deep-fry beef until it is seared. Drain.
Reheat 2 tablespoons of oil in wok.
Add onions.
Stir-fry until soft and well-browned, about 20 minutes.
Add beef.
Add sherry, sugar and soy sauce.
Stir-fry 1 minute, until beef is glazed and brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll and press together crescent rolls to cover cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool completely.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread evenly over crust.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, sugar, oil, eggs and pineapple by hand.
Add bananas, nuts and raisins and mix again. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool in pan 1 hour before removing.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, melt together the chocolate pieces and butter.
Gradually add the powdered sugar and evaporated milk, stirring constantly.
Bring the mixture to boiling; reduce heat. Cook, stirring constantly, for 8 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in the vanilla.
Let the sauce stand for 10 minutes. Makes 1 1/2 cups of sauce.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Place dip in ovenproof serving dish that has been coated with cooking spray and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve hot with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat and saute onions until clear. Grease a 2-quart casserole dish with 1 tablespoon of margarine. Reserve 12 saltine crackers.
Crumble for topping.
Line dish with remaining cracker crumbs.
Add onions and soup in alternate layers until dish is full.
Cover top with eggs and pour milk over top. Spread grated cheese and cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry ham
directions: Heat cranberry sauce in saucepan over medium heat until hot. Cut ham slices in half.
Place in 7 x 11-inch baking dish, overlapping edges.
Pour hot cranberry sauce over top.
Bake, covered, with foil at 325° until heated through.
Do not overbake. Garnish with orange slices.

title: guilt-free "mounds" bar
directions: Combine; spread in small pan.
Freeze until solid.
Cut in squares.
Eat frozen.

title: lemon punch
directions: Combine sugar and 2 cups water.
Heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cool. Add remaining 2 cups water, lemon peel and juice. Chill.
Pour into chilled punch bowl. Add scoops of sherbet, stirring until partially melted.
Pour ginger ale down side of bowl, stirring with up and down motion.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine wine, clam juice, thyme and water; bring to a boil. Add scallops to boiling liquid; cook until scallops are firm. Drain scallops and cool.
When scallops have cooled, mix with shrimp and crabmeat.
Add peppers, onion, cilantro, dill, juice of 2 lemons and vinaigrette.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve cold.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cheese bars
directions: Open 1 package crescent rolls; place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, spreading to cover bottom of pan.
Pinch perforations together.
Mix other ingredients and spread on rolls.
Cover with other package of rolls.
Brush top with egg white.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: In a medium saucepan over low heat, add both bags of morsels. Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
When morsels are completely melted, remove from burner and add the nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Remove from wax paper.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.
Enjoy!

title: cardinal casserole
directions: In medium bowl, place bread crumbs, bird seed mix and green grapes, cut in pieces.
Set aside.
Put beef suet through meat grinder, then into double boiler to melt.
Remove from heat; allow to cool and harden slightly.
Reheat and while in liquid form, pour 1 1/2 cups over dry ingredients.
Add sand.
Mix well with fork.
Turn into a foil loaf size pan (5 x 3 x 1-inch). Refrigerate until firm.
Place on feeder tray.

title: sour cream pound cake #2
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar a little at a time.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar (white); bring to boil.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach pie
directions: Brush bottom of pie crust with egg white to prevent sogginess. Wash spinach, break into bite sized pieces.
Fry bacon and break into pieces.
Slice mushrooms.
Layer ingredients into pie crust, beginning with spinach, then bacon or pepperoni, mushrooms, cheeses and top with uncooked bacon or more pepperoni.
This will be very tall but it sinks as it bakes.
To prevent spinach from falling off pie shell, wrap a long piece of foil, 35 inches long, around the pie plate, forming a circular wall.
The wall will be as tall as the width of your foil, 12 inches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crisp bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions with salt and 2-quarts cracked ice. Let stand, covered, with a weighted lid for 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly and put in a large kettle.
Add sugar, spices and vinegar.
Bring almost to a boil, stirring often with a wooden spoon.
Don't let it boil!
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: grandmother cole's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix by hand adding apples and nuts last.
Sprinkle butterscotch bits on top.
Bake at 325° in a 13-inch Pyrex dish for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet muffin mix
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat eggs; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove immediately from pan.

title: cranberry-grape salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar and let stand overnight.
Drain. Add marshmallows, grapes and nuts.
Just before serving, fold in Cool Whip.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cheese and marshmallow cream until well blended.
Serve with desired fresh fruit.

title: poor man steak
directions: Mix ingredients except soup.
Put on cookie sheet; press down to 1 1/2-inches.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into pieces. Flour and brown in skillet.
Put in a baking dish.
Pour soup over meat.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. (Tastes like Salisbury Steak.)

title: 3 step cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla well.
Blend in eggs.
Add 1/2 cup mini semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Pour into ready-mix graham crust.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (almost set).
Cool for 3 hours.

title: aunt polly's chess pie
directions: Beat eggs together; add rest of ingredients and beat until mixed well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until set.
If crust starts getting too brown, lay a sheet of tinfoil over pie until done.

title: microwave cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an 8-inch pie plate. Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes until cheese melts, stirring twice during cooking.
Serve with corn chips.

title: mango trifle
directions: Slice swiss cake rolls into 1/2-inch pieces, line in a Pyrex dish in a single layer.
Mix all of cream,
condensed milk, and cream cheese and beat until well mixed.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan; stir in water and peaches.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring gently. Remove from heat; stir in butter, lemon rind and juice and almond extract.
Cool.
Prepare unbaked pie crust; add peach mixture. Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pat in the pan pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press firmly and evenly against bottom and side of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: kraut
directions: Cover cabbage with hot spigot water for 1 hour (not boiling); drain and pack into hot jars.
Add the vinegar, salt and sugar. Cover with boiling water.
Using hot lids, seal.
Makes delicious kraut.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put dry rice in bottom of pan.	Pour in soup and 1 soup can of	water.	Stir.
Add
chicken.
Sprinkle	all spices on top. Cover
with foil and bake at 350° for an hour to an hour and a half.

title: steak and potatoes
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Place in electric skillet and brown. After browning meat, turn heat down to medium.
Slice onion, pepper and potatoes and place over meat.
Cook until done.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Cover and let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken with cheese
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Dip in egg, then in bread crumbs and brown in butter.
Cook well.
Saute onions in 1/2 stick butter until soft (5 minutes).
Add broth and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour cream and onion mixture in blender and puree.
Cover chicken with sauce and grated cheese and broil until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together butter, pretzels and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into bottom of baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Cool, then mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Spread onto cooled pretzel mixture.
In bowl, mix Jell-O and hot water until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add in thawed strawberries. Refrigerate until slightly jelled.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: harvest sweet potato soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or kettle, saute celery and onion in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat; simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Discard the bay leaf.
Cool slightly.
In a blender or food processor, process soup in batches until smooth.
Return all to pan and heat through.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon pieces and saute onion.
Remove excess bacon drippings from pan.
Add Milnot mixed with water to equal 4 cups of liquid.
Add potatoes and carrots and simmer until veggies are soft but firm.
Add all corn and simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt these together on medium heat and pour up!
Great with nachos.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar together, saving 2 tablespoons for topping.
Press graham cracker mixture in bottom of pan.
Combine Dream Whip and marshmallows; spoon 1/2 of this over crumbs.
Top with pie filling.
Add rest of marshmallow mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: strawberry banana pie
directions: Whip the Dream Whip and set in refrigerator.
Mix the jello with 2 cups water.
Stir in the frozen strawberries.
Put jello mixture in refrigerator until it jells.
Combine the jello mixture and Dream Whip.
Fold in the bananas.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and chill for 24 hours.
Serve with vegetables.

title: pistachio cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Grated nuts can be added to flour mix also.

title: shish touk(lebanese chicken kabob)
directions: Cut chicken into approximately 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Combine all other ingredients in shallow pan.
Add chicken to marinade. Place, covered, in refrigerator for at least one full day.
Thread chicken pieces onto skewers and cook on barbecue grill, rotating skewers and brushing with marinade frequently, until done.
(May also cook chicken under broiler indoors.)

title: broccoli amon deluxe
directions: Cook cut broccoli as directed. Drain. Cook onions in boiling water till tender. Drain. In same pan melt 1/2 of the butter. Blend in flour, salt, and dash of pepper. Add milk, cook, stirring constantly till thickened and bubbly. Reduce heat. Blend in cream cheese till smooth. Place vegetables in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole. Pour sauce mixture over and mix lightly. Add American cheese. Add reminding butter (melted). Mix with bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° till heated through, about 40 to 45 minutes. 6 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together, then add to the Jell-O with hot water.
Don't mix Jell-O and water until last because it sets fast.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Combine and beat all ingredients together.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add other ingredients; mix well. Cook in Bundt pan at 350° approximately 1 hour until done.

title: chicken steak
directions: Pound the chicken in order to tenderize it.
Pour half of the Worcestershire sauce on the breast and add the seasonings. Tenderize until chicken is thin and flat.
Broil both sides and add the rest of the sauce.
This makes 1 serving.

title: dorothy's raised potato doughnuts
directions: Heat the 2 cups of milk; add sugar, shortening, salt and mashed potato.
Cool until lukewarm and add yeast, eggs and cinnamon.
Add about 8 cups of flour.
Mix and knead; let rise. Punch down; turn onto board and cut doughnuts.
Cook in hot oil until golden brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter in saucepan.
Boil and cook approximately 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Pour in all at once.
Stir immediately over popcorn.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring frequently. Makes about 20 servings.

title: make ahead sausage casserole
directions: Arrange bread slices in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Saute sausage and drain.
Combine with mustard and sprinkle over bread (which can be day old).
Place cheese over sausage.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Is nice for brunch when having company.
Serves 8.

title: bed and breakfast tortillas
directions: In skillet, cook sausage over medium heat, stirring to crumble; drain and set aside.
Add eggs to skillet and scramble.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
When eggs are set, add sausage. Remove from heat and add cheese.
Warm tortillas, one at a time, in microwave, 10 seconds each.
Spread 1 tablespoon picante sauce down center of each tortilla.
Divide egg mixture among tortillas.
Fold bottom 1/3 of tortilla over filling.
Fold sides toward center and overlap.
Makes 6.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Place with other ingredients in pan; cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Boil water with cinnamon sticks and cloves; add tea bags and steep for 10 minutes.
Remove spices.
Add orange juice, lemonade and sugar.
Good hot or cold.

title: modesta potatoes
directions: Note:
May need more butter depending on potatoes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut in small pieces.
Cut corn from cob. Dice peppers, celery, carrots and okra.
Combine all ingredients and cook in a large pot for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook at low heat.
Pour in jars and pressure at 10 pounds for 15 minutes.

title: lasagna seafood style
directions: Combine tuna, crab, soups, pepper and milk.
Cook noodles. Butter the dish, then put a layer of noodles, 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Place cheese squares on top.
Repeat, then sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together.
Bake in 3 greased cake pans at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until turning brown; drain fat off.
Pour onion rings and brown them.
Mix everything together and bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: patriotic gelatin salad
directions: In four separate bowls, dissolve each package of gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to each and stir.
Pour one bowl of blue gelatin into an oiled 10-inch fluted tube pan; chill until almost set, about 30 minutes.
Set other three bowls of gelatin aside at room temperature.
Soften unflavored gelatin in remaining cold water; let stand 5 minutes.
Heat milk in a saucepan over medium heat just below boiling.
Stir in softened gelatin and sugar until sugar is dissolved.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: In frying pan, cook bacon until lightly browned.
Add onions. Cook until tender; drain and set aside.

title: chip beef cheese ball
directions: Dice the green pepper, onion and chip beef together.
Take cheese at room temperature and place on board.
Mix ingredients by hand into cheese mixture.
After thoroughly mixing, form into ball.
Roll onto nuts or crushed Ritz crackers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook all together for 10 minutes, stirring several times.
Add 2 tablespoons liquid smoke.
Cook 10 more minutes; pour in jars and seal.

title: candied pecans
directions: Beat egg white until frothy.
Pour into nuts and stir until moistened.
Stir and mix well the last 3 ingredients.
Pour over nuts; stir until coated.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 250° about 1 hour.
Stir and turn nuts 3 times while baking.
Do not overbake.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat after each addition.
Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Add carrots, pineapple (do not drain) and nuts.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: pressed pecan pie crust
directions: Melt oleo and pour over flour in pie pan.
Add nuts.
Press in pan.
Bake and cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture with bananas.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: russian chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in butter in large skillet (10 minutes).
Add 1/4 cup water; bring to boil. Lower heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, or until tender. Transfer to warm platter; keep warm.
Scrape up any browned bits from skillet.
Cook mushrooms, tomato, green onions and thyme in skillet for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle vegetables with flour; stir to mix well and cook 1 minute.
Crumble bouillon cube into skillet.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup water.
Continue stirring until bouillon is dissolved and mixture smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until thickened and bubbly (3 minutes).
Pour over chicken and serve with noodles.

title: chinese turkey salad
directions: In small saucepan, over medium heat, heat mustard, orange juice, green onion, oil, honey, soy sauce and ginger for 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through; keep warm. On large serving platter, layer salad greens, pea pods, orange segments, water chestnuts, turkey strips and noodles. Serve salad drizzled with warm mustard dressing.

title: belgian salad
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to boil, let cool, add olive oil.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients with the exception of the chocolate chips. Let this come to a rapid boil and boil exactly one minute.
Do not boil any longer or frosting will get too hard.
After boiling, take off heat and add chocolate chips and stir until all chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour over brownies that have cooled.
This mixture is best used in a
13 x 9-inch pan.

title: potato salad(serves about 75)
directions: Cook potatoes and eggs.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In 1-quart, shallow casserole, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered at 300° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Scald milk and oleo.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add sugar and salt.
Add oats to hot milk and wait for mixture to cool. Mix all together and gradually add flour.
Mix well and proceed as for all yeast breads.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheesy sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, soup, Cheddar, salt, pepper and onion together.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top. Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°, then remove cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: pina colada muffins
directions: Prepare cake mix as package directs.
Add other ingredients. Mix 1 minute; do not overbeat.
Grease muffin tins or line with paper cups; fill about 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until golden and muffins spring back when touched. Serves 25.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and break into 1/4-inch pieces.
Saute onions in bacon fat until tender.
Add green pepper, celery, tomatoes and salt.
Cook until vegetables are tender and sauce thickens, about 15 minutes.
Add peas, shrimp and chili powder and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add the cooked bacon. Pack rice into a greased 9-inch tube pan.
Carefully turn rice out on a serving platter.
Pour sauce in center and around the ring.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (no mixer needed). Put in pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: non-fat muffins(serves 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray or line with paper cups.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add peanut butter.
Mix on high.
Add more milk if needed.

title: whole wheat banana sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firmly set. Cool.
Remove from pan and cut into sticks.
Put onto a cookie sheet and bake at 150° for 1 hour longer until sticks are hard and crunchy.
Store in tightly covered container.
Yield:
35 servings.

title: unbelievable cookies
directions: Combine sugar and peanut butter in a large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Dough will be dry.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll in hand 1-inch balls.
Place balls on cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Slightly mash each ball with a fork (crisscross).
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken or spareribs
directions: Saute until brown 1/4 cup onions in 1 tablespoon drippings or other fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: padre island sand dollars
directions: Beat butter or oleo and powdered sugar until fluffy. Gradually mix in flour.
Stir in vanilla and salt and mix well. Using level tablespoonful of dough, shape into balls.
Press one side of each ball into granulated sugar.
Place sugar sides up on ungreased cookie sheet.
Can be close together, they do not spread.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Do not brown.
Remove from pan, cool on rack.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Stir in lemon juice.
Cool and add 1 pint whip cream whipped.
Add fruit (oranges, bananas, cherries, strawberries, apples and pineapple chunks).

title: rolled ginger cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Beat in egg, molasses and vinegar.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend in. Chill 3 hours.

title: hamburger bake("quickie dinner")
directions: Mold hamburger meat as a flat hamburger on foil.
Cut potato in strips and place over hamburger.
Cut up onion and green pepper and place over potato.
Salt to taste.
Cook 1 hour at 400°.
Open foil and sprinkle with cheese the last 5 minutes.
Serve with ketchup!

title: ollie's pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder well (3 times).
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then mix in the sour cream or cream cheese.
Combine flour mixture with the liquid mixture. Mix well until you do not feel the sugar grains.
Add the vanilla and lemon extract.
Add mace spice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done when tested using the toothpick method.

title: sugar plums
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Let chill in refrigerator, then melt chips and paraffin in double boiler and dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on foil or wax paper until cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in shallow 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover with chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Top with crumbs.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: diabetic fruit and yogurt shake
directions: In a blender container, combine undrained peaches, banana, yogurt and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes; cover and blend until frothy.
Makes 2 (1 1/4 cups) servings.
In testing, we discovered that if we added a little vanilla to this shake, we did not need a sweetener.

title: honey-spiced chicken with orange sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet until hot.
Cook chicken over medium heat until brown on all sides, about 15 minutes.
Place chicken in ungreased, oblong baking dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch.
Tip with onions.
Sprinkle with salt, paprika and pepper.
Mix orange juice, honey, lemon juice, ginger and nutmeg.
Pour over chicken. Add olives.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven until thickest pieces of chicken are done, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: traci's no bake yogurt pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt.
Pour into graham cracker shell. Chill one hour.
Approximately 4 g fat per slice, or use light yogurt for less fat.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Add syrup, butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: french canoe(main meal)
directions: Cut loaf of bread lengthwise.
Scrape out inside of bread, leaving an inch shell, like two canoes.
Brown the chuck and drain.
Add sour cream and mushrooms.
Put meat mixture into the bread shells.
Top with grated cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Dump beans into a large casserole dish (or use any 3 favorite beans) . Brown and drain ground meat and onion.
Add to beans and sliced sausage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sunny coleslaw dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour over cabbage and toss. Heap coleslaw in salad bowl and border with carrots.

title: homemade flap jacks
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in bowl and add the milk to desired consistency.
Pour into greased skillet and fry, flipping once until done.

title: chili
directions: Fry meat until crumbly; add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle a little flour to thicken sauce.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove stems.
Place tops, hollow side up, in a pan lined with butter.
Chop stems and mix them with half the fine bread crumbs and a little melted butter.
Thoroughly mix in eggs, cream and Parmesan cheese.
Fill the hollows of the mushroom caps; pour over them a little melted butter, a few bread crumbs and salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until light brown.

title: smoked sausage pilaf
directions: Mix and pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: upside-down pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl blend together and place in an 8 x 14-inch pan the filling, sugar, spices, eggs and milk.
Sprinkle over top of dry cake mix and nuts.
Pour melted oleo over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. If not done, turn off oven and let set for 10 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spray a 1-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray. Slice boiled egg.
Grate cheese.
Layer ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook the sugar and pears approximately 1 hour until it looks clear and the syrup is thick. Add the pineapple.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: old-fashioned potato pie
directions: Wash potatoes (then boil in their skins until very soft). Peel and mash.
Add listed ingredients and stir well.
Use unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven or until golden brown.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar to boiling.
Remove from heat and add jello and cream cheese.
Mix until cream cheese is dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
When cooled, add ice water and nuts.
Whip chilled can of milk and fold into mixture.
Put in a large mold and chill overnight.
Serves 15.
Preparation: 30 minutes.

title: little wellingtons
directions: Saute filet slices in butter or oil unti lightly browned, cool. Saute onion and mushrooms in meat drippings.
Add sherry and reduce slightly.
Roll out patty shell until large enough to Cover meat. Place filet in the center of the pastry.
Top with tablespoons of mushroom mixture.
Cover meat.
Seal pastry with water.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: great aunt ama's carrots
directions: Boil fresh carrots or canned.
Grease baking dish.
Layer carrots, apple, butter, sugar and nutmeg.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, margarine and sugar in medium size saucepan. Slowly bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil five minutes. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir vigorously.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish or pan. Cool and cut in squares.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Coat 8 by 4 inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Combine sour cream, milk, sugar, oil, beaten egg, lemon juice and lemon zest in medium bowl.
Stir sour cream mixture into flour mixture until well combined; pour batter into prepared loaf pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cake cool in pan on wire rack 20 to 25 minutes before removing from pan; cool completely on wire rack.
Slice cake and serve with washed strawberries.
Cover any leftover cake with plastic wrap and store tightly sealed in the refrigerator.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Combine cornstarch with milk in a small bowl and stir until cornstarch has dissolved.
Add cheez whiz and stir.
Microwave on high for 1 minute stir until smooth.
Add juice from jalapenos; stir well.

title: french beef stew
directions: In heavy saucepan or casserole, put all ingredients, except peas and wine; do not brown meat.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cover mixture in pan and watch until it starts to bubble.
Turn down heat to 250° and bake for 4 1/2 hours.
Lift cover and gently press in package of frozen peas; do not stir at all.
Return to oven and bake for 1/2 hour.
Just before serving, add 1/2 cup dry red wine.
Feeds 8.

title: homemade butter rolls
directions: Stir yeast, 2 Tbsp. sugar and 2 cups warm water in a 4-cup glass measuring cup; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir together yeast mixture, butter and remaining sugar in a large bowl;
stir in eggs and salt.
Gradually stir in enough flour to make a soft dough. Cover and chill eight hours.

title: country meat loaf
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, saute oil, onions and celery.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally with slotted spoon.
In large bowl, tear bread slices.
Add onion and celery mixture.
Add ground beef, carrot, salt, pepper, egg and 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Stir thoroughly to mix.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, shape ground beef mixture into 8 x 4-inch loaf; set aside.

title: chicken-henny penny
directions: Mix all ingredients together well except the last 2.
Put in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle the cheese on top of mixture.
Add potato chips on top of cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: tostados
directions: Brown the beef, salt and pepper.
Add beans to beef and simmer.
Warm tomato sauce and taco sauce, mixed together, in a separate pan.
Cut lettuce fine, chop tomatoes and grate cheese.

title: kolaches
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water and stir to dissolve, then add the milk.
Sift flour with salt.
Work in half the flour and beat until smooth.
Cream butter, gradually add the sugar.
When light and fluffy, blend into first mixture.
Add the egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Work in the remaining flour by hand.
Add only enough flour to make a light dough.
Place dough in a greased bowl.
Grease top of dough with some melted butter, cover, let rise in warm place until double in bulk (2 to 2 1/2 hours).
Punch dough down, then turn out on lightly floured board and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in circles and place 1 1/2 inches apart on buttered baking sheet. Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 1/2 hour.

title: swedish kallops(braised beef)
directions: Roll meat in mixture of flour, salt, pepper and brown sugar. Put shortening in kettle and brown meat, turning occasionally. Add a small amount of water, replacing if necessary.
Add bay leaf, allspice and peppercorns.
Cook on low heat 2 hours or until tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, pecans, celery, seasoning salt and onion.
Roll into a ball.
Chill. Serve with crackers.
(I prefer "Chicken In A Biskit".)
Ball freezes well.

title: rumaki
directions: You also need toothpicks.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan, on low heat, melt margarine, marshmallows and oil.
DON'T overheat.
Pour over popcorn and stir.
Wet hands; shape mixture into 2 1/2 inch balls.
Wrap in wax paper and store in loosely covered container.
DO NOT refrigerate

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: 7 hour salad
directions: Layer ingredients in long Pyrex or Tupperware container in order as listed, beginning with lettuce and ending with mayonnaise.
As the last layer, sprinkle bacon bits on top. Cover tightly and let stand in refrigerator at least 7 hours, overnight is better.
Toss about one hour before serving time.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Combine sugar and butter. Mix well. Add egg. Mix well. Add flour, salt, oats, sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Mix well. Add gumdrops and nuts. Drop teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: green tomato cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large mixer bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla, beat well.
Stir in the drained grated tomatoes and pour into a greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat butter or margarine and shortening for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture; beat well.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Working with half the dough at a time, on lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut with cookie or biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream cheese and butter after you grate cheese.
Work other ingredients in with hand.
Run through cookie press.
(I use the one with ridges on top.)
Bake 10 minutes, watch they will burn real easy.
They are better not real brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and margarine well.
Add sugar, a little at a time, and continue creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients; beat well.
Fold in coconut.
Bake in a large tube pan for about 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Let cool in pan at least 15 minutes.
This cake needs no icing.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and shortening; press firmly on the bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook to softball stage at 234°.
Add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheese cake stollen(easy)
directions: Lay out crescent rolls on ungreased cookie sheet, overlapping points.
Mix together other ingredients and place in middle of rolls.
Fold 2 exposed points of rolls over mixture and pinch together.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans, rinse and drain again.
Combine beans, celery, onions, olives, seasonings and salad dressing.
Mix; chill 2 hours or overnight is better.
At serving time, drain and add mayonnaise and eggs.
Mix carefully to avoid mashing beans.
Garnish with lettuce and serve.

title: west virginia pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and press into a 10-inch pie pan or glass baking dish.
Bake shell 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix half of the Cool Whip with the softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread in crust.
Mix the instant pudding and milk together.
Spread over cheese and nut mix.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Serve cooled.

title: peach bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and almond extract.
Mix together flour, salt, 1 teaspoon soda and baking powder; add together; fold in peaches.
Grease and flour pans (2 loaf or 1 Bundt pan).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.

title: fern's mistletoe salad
directions: Drain and mix.
Should stand overnight.
The longer it sits the better it is.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: In blender blend beans and juice. Add sugar slowly.
Add eggs, blend.
Add margarine and blend.
Stir in nuts. Pour into the 3 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: great grandma's jello salad
directions: In medium bowl, mix cottage cheese, pineapple, Jell-O and nuts.
Let set in icebox for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except peaches, sugar and cream cheese.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 8 or 10-inch pie plate.
Drain peaches, reserving juice.
Place peaches over batter.

title: microwave potato soup
directions: Microwave potatoes, onion and water in covered 2-quart glass casserole, 16 to 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Combine milk and flour.
Stir into vegetable mixture along with remaining ingredients.

title: tuna casserole(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix all together, place half in casserole dish, top with sour cream then add remaining mixture.
Top with crushed potato chips.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook onion in butter.
