Add remaining ingredients and simmer until cheese melts.
Serve with chips and crackers.

title: cheese bunnies
directions: You will need a round cookie cutter for this recipe.

title: seafoam(candy)
directions: Butter sides of heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
In it combine sugars, water, corn syrup and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling.
Then cook to hard ball stage (250°) without stirring.
Remove from heat. Immediately beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot syrup in a thin stream over beaten egg whites, beating constantly, at high speed on electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture forms soft peak and begins to lose its gloss, about 10 minutes. Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper, swirling each candy to a peak.

title: seafood crepes
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Add egg.
Gradually add milk; mix until smooth.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Heat pan; grease well. Pour 2 to 3 tablespoons batter into pan.
Cook slowly until batter is set and lightly browned.
Turn; brown second side.
Makes 4 pancakes.

title: busy day dinner
directions: Place all ingredients in order given, into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on each layer and dot with butter. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onions which have been sliced into 1/4-inch slices.
Saute until clear; reserve 3 tablespoons of crushed crackers for topping.
Line casserole dish with crushed Ritz crackers; add onion and soup alternately.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Pour over casserole; top with cheese and remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until top is brown and bubbling.

title: easy peanut chews
directions: Prepare pie crust
mix according to package directions. Blend in brown sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and 1/2 cup chopped peanuts. Spread
on well-greased baking sheet to 13 x 10-inch rectangle. Bake
at
350° until done, about 15 to 17 minutes. Loosen edges as soon as the cookies are removed from the oven. Cool
the
cookies on	the sheet.
Cut the cookies in bars or squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes, remove from heat.
Add small amount to egg yolks, stirring remaining hot mixture.
Cook 1 minute.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: jan's praline bars
directions: Break each graham cracker into 4 sections.
Line bottom of 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 jelly roll pan with graham crackers; close.
Grease pan if not Teflon.
Bring butter and sugar to rolling boil; boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour evenly over crackers. Smooth with spoon.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let cool few minutes only.
Lift out with spatula onto wax paper.
Let cool completely.
Break into sections when cool.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 3/4 cup peach juice and 1/4 cup cherry juice.
In saucepan, add remaining ingredients to reserved peach and cherry juice.
Heat until smooth and thickened.
Pour sauce over fruit.
Bake at 350° until hot (approximately 20 minutes).
A favorite at holiday breakfast or brunch.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil, cool and cube potatoes.
Saute in 3/4 of the butter, the green pepper, onion and parsley, then mix with the potatoes.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan with casserole dish.
Pat with butter and sprinkle with cheese and bacon.

title: kathryn's pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll.
Makes 1 large or 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, milk, garlic salt, salt and pepper and form into 1-inch balls.
Brown balls slightly in vegetable oil.
Cover and cook on low for 5 minutes.
Drain excess oil.
In another pan, combine chili sauce and jelly.
Heat until jelly turns to liquid.
Pour over meatballs.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Pour into crock-pot and cook 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: pear and grape salad
directions: Cover salad plate with leaf lettuce.
Place pear half, flat side down.
Mix cream cheese and cream and spread all over pear. Cut grapes in half and place flat side down on the covered pear, close together to resemble a bunch of grapes.
Place a piece of grape stem under the end of pear.
Serve with French dressing on the side in a little tiny glass container.

title: corn bread
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together until thickened.
Add margarine, sugar, eggs and salt.
Stir to mix.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 425° for about 1 hour.

title: cheese-beef pie
directions: Cook beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off pan drippings; stir in tomato sauce, chilies, chili powder and garlic salt.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, over low heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Combine egg, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and sour cream; mix well.
Add to meat mixture, stirring well; set aside. Separate each biscuit into two halves, making 20 biscuit rounds. Press 10 rounds into a greased 8-inch baking dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Cover with remaining biscuit rounds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: 3 bean hot dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place beef, onion and bacon in large saucepan.
Cook, stirring with fork to break up meat until brown. Pour off drippings.
Add beans, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon in a large baking dish.
Top with 3 to 4 slices of bacon and bake one hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil, add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, then zucchini and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes after removing from oven.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak in strips and dust in flour.
Brown in butter, then add chopped onion, mushrooms and beef broth.
Simmer slowly until meat is tender (about 1/2 to 3/4 hour).
Add 1/2 pint sour cream.
Pour over one half of 8 ounce package cooked noodles.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain.
Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Combine with oatmeal and raisins and mix well.
Add flour mixed with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking pans and bake at 350° to 375° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini spice bread
directions: Grease and flour bottom of loaf pan.
Beat oil, egg and milk together.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Do not beat.
Fold in nuts and zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool before cutting.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Freezes well.

title: sour cream shrimp curry
directions: Saute the onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in the sour cream, curry, salt and pepper along with the cooked shrimp.
Heat slowly and serve over rice.

title: aunt pat's summer salad
directions: Peel, seed and chop cucumbers.
Chop zucchini.
Toss cucumber and zucchini with 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 cup vinegar.
Sit for 30 minutes.
Peel, seed and chop tomatoes.
Drain cucumbers and zucchini and toss with tomatoes and onions.
Add vinegar and oil to taste, season with salt and pepper and toss with mint and parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pampered pane
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread) together until well blended.
Cover bread halves well to edges with spread.
Top with grated cheese (Jack, Cheddar, Velveeta or Parmesan). Sprinkle with chopped parsley for garnish. Slip under broiler until brown and bubbly. Slice and serve.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese together in bowl.
Dip each piece of chicken in melted butter and then in cheese mixture. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This is great served with rice and a vegetable.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Mash bananas and add to mixture.
Mix in vanilla and pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with the fruit of your choice.

title: liz's yummy cookie bars
directions: In 350° oven, melt butter, press graham cracker crumbs down firmly in 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes until golden brown.
Pour Eagle Brand over crumbs, sprinkle chips over top and nuts and coconut.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesy sausage biscuit
directions: Crumble sausage into a large skillet.
Add onion and cook over medium heat until sausage is browned.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients are moistened.
Drop by heaping tablespoons about 1 inch apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Dice onions and pepper.
Cook briefly in about 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Put this in heavy kettle; add tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cayenne, if desired.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Ten minutes before serving, add curry powder.
Mixture should be cooked until quite thick.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream Wesson oil and sugar; add eggs.
Blend in molasses; add soda, dissolved in hot water.
Sift together flour, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture and stir well.
Add boiling water. Turn into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Serve with whipped cream and cherry on top.

title: pineapple sex cake
directions: Bake cake from box directions.
Mix pineapple and pudding (from directions) together.
Put on top of cooled cake.
Mix cream cheese and whipped cream together.
Put in refrigerator.
Layer: Cooled cake, pineapple and pudding and cream cheese and whipped cream.

title: "fat-free" chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes. Makes 16 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes and hot dogs
directions: Place potatoes, onion and enough water to cover in a large saucepan; cook until tender.
Meanwhile, melt butter in another saucepan.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add milk and cheese, stirring until cheese melts and sauce is thickened.
Add hot dogs and heat through.
Drain potatoes and onion; place in a baking dish.
Add sauce and mix to distribute hot dogs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(I usually can make 2 casseroles out of this, one to eat and one to freeze.
My kids love this.)

title: chutney roll
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and shape into a roll. Chill.
Serve on platter with assorted crackers.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Cook onion and celery in chicken broth; strain.
Add bouillon. Mix flour, Crisco, salt and baking powder until size of peas.
Add enough water to make a soft mixture.
Roll thin, using lots of flour.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Drop in boiling liquid; cook until almost done.
Add chicken and finish cooking.
Add 1/2 stick oleo and a little milk.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump canned goods and cake mix together in a bowl.
Mix lightly.
Dump into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef tenderloin ragout
directions: Saute beef in butter.
Add flour and garlic.
Place in roaster pan.
Combine beef stock, wine, water, pepper, salt, bay leaf and marjoram.
Pour over beef.
Cover roaster pan.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 1/2 hours until beef is done.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Return to oven until mushrooms are just tender.

title: crepes
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix.
Pour 1/4 cup batter for each crepe into hot nonstick pan.
Cook until top is full of bubbles, edges dry and underside browned.
Turn and brown second side.
May be cooked ahead of time and stored in refrigerator for reheating at time of serving.

title: pineapple walnut cake
directions: Mix by hand in large bowl.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spiced chicken and pea pods
directions: Put all ingredients in the order listed.
Cook in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan; bring to boil. Full boil for 1 minute.
Add oats and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Cool and enjoy.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in stock with onions until soft.
Place in blender and blend quickly, leaving small pieces of broccoli.
Make a roux using butter and flour.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and stock to roux.
To avoid lumps, stir constantly until thickened.
Thin to preferred consistency with cream.
Add seasoning.
Garnish.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Saute onion in butter. Blend in cream cheese. Stir in next 5 ingredients.
In another bowl, mix soup, milk and wine.
Fold in seafood. In
greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put 3 noodles side by side to make a single layer. Spread 1/3 cheese mixture and 1/3 seafood mixture. Repeat 2 more times.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (covered). Top with Cheddar cheese and bake, uncovered, 15 minutes more or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: macaroni supper
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend soup and milk together. Add to macaroni mixture with 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400°
for 20 minutes.

title: hershey's chocolate candy(makes 5 pounds)
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook very slowly; let boil 6 minutes. Remove from heat and drop in oleo and chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into large pan.
Let stand 6 hours before cutting.

title: old-time beef stew
directions: Heat shortening in Dutch oven or 6-quart pot.
Add beef; brown 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except for potatoes, carrots, cold water and flour.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours. Then add vegetables and simmer until tender.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo until it spins a thread.
Add raw peanuts.
Cook until peanuts are done.
Add soda.
Pour in greased pans really thin.

title: apple strudel
directions: Mix water, egg and melted butter, add salt.
On a floured board work the liquid mixture into the flour, kneading until the dough is very elastic and no longer sticks to board.
Cover with a warm bowl and let stand one hour.
Meanwhile, prepare the filling.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until translucent.
In pot, add 5 cups water, bouillon cubes and onions.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: dill crackers
directions: Warm oil in oblong dish; add dry ingredients and stir well to coat crackers.
Bake at 200° for 20 to 25 minutes; stir every few minutes.
Store in covered container.

title: cheese and sausage hot dip
directions: Cut up cheese into squares and place in microwave bowl. Add both cans. Cook and mince sausage. Add to mixture and microwave 10 minutes on High, then stir. Cook another 5 minutes. Stir and serve with tortilla chips.

title: cranberry nut pinwheel cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Beat until light and fluffy, scraping the bowl occasionally.
Combine dry ingredients; add to the creamed mixture.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Stir in pineapple, 1 cup pecans, pepper, onion and salt.
Put in refrigerator until hard enough to shape into balls.
Divide in half.
Shape into two balls.
Roll in remaining pecans.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onion and ground meat together until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Stir well. Serves 6.

title: broccoli rice
directions: In a skillet, saute onion, margarine and celery.
Add frozen broccoli and cook until well thawed.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Combine with cooked rice.
Place mixture in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with toasted bread crumbs and bake for about 15 minutes longer.
(All baking is done with pans uncovered.)

title: bayou pecan and rice dessert
directions: Put rice, water and salt in a 2-quart saucepan. Bring to a vigorous boil. Then heat down to low. Cover with lid. Simmer over this low heat 14 minutes. Remove saucepan from heat but leave the lid on 10 minutes. While rice cooks, mix together the eggs, dark syrup, sugar, vanilla and butter. After the rice cooks, stir in the milk. Cover and cook over low heat until the milk is absorbed. Stir occasionally. Press the rice over the bottom of a glass pie plate or shallow baking dish, holding about 6 cups. Just before baking, pour the egg-syrup mixture over the rice. Sprinkle with the pecans. Push the pecans into the syrup mixture. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes. Serve warm. Top with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream, if desired. This recipe makes 8 generous servings.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Cream cheese and oleo.
Add flour, salt and cayenne.
Knead in Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten and crisscross with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: georgia cobbler
directions: Stir together sugar, Crisco, flour, salt, baking powder and milk in the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Mix fruit, sugar and fruit juice together and pour over the batter.
Dot the batter with butter and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine beaten eggs, milk and butter.
Beat in flour, salt and baking powder with a whisk. Add spinach and cheese and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased glass baking pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: goulash soup
directions: Fry onions in hot fat until transparent.
Add green peppers and tomato paste.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add meat and remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Add cubed potatoes, if you like and simmer until potatoes are done.
Best served the second day.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt butter and add to softened cream cheese; add powdered sugar until you have a firm texture.
Add extract.
Blend well.

title: summer vegetables
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and pepper in margarine until limp. Add tomatoes, zucchini, corn, salt, sugar and pepper.
Heat until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and milk until smooth.
Stir into hot mixture.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into a baking dish and top with French fried onion rings.
Brown briefly under the broiler.

title: apple crisp(blueberry crisp)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill 8 x 8-inch baking dish with peeled, cored and sliced apples.
In a small bowl combine all dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and toss until crumbly.
Spread over fruit.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Top with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar, milk and cinnamon; beat until smooth.
Pour into melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour in large can of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cornstarch finger paint
directions: Bring water to a boil. Dissolve cornstarch in water, stirring well. Bring to a boil again. Cooled paint will be slightly thicker; good for brush painting as well as finger painting.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar slowly while beating.
Add chocolate bits and nuts; blend.
Put on cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Place cookies in oven.
Turn oven off; leave overnight.
Do not open the door.

title: oriental shrimp for two
directions: Thaw shrimp according to package directions.
Prepare rice according to package directions.

title: trey's peppermint candy
directions: Line a baking sheet with foil and set aside.
Heat baking pieces or candy coating in a heavy 2 qt. saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly till melted and smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir 1/3 c. crushed candy.
Pour mixture onto prepared baking sheet, spreading to about a 10 in. circle.
Sprinkle with 2 tbsp. crushed candy.
Chill about 30 minutes or until firm.
Use the foil to lift candy from the baking sheet, break candy into pieces. Store, tightly covered, in the refrigerator.
Makes about 1 1/4 lb.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and egg. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pecans on top of cake.
Cream together butter, eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and chop.
Reserve caps.
Saute veggies and mushroom stems in 1/4 cup margarine in a skillet until tender.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, wine, salt and pepper.

title: mary kaulfus' refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add flour, soda, salt and buttermilk.
Mix until smooth.
Meanwhile, pour boiling water over 100% bran.
Let stand until cereal has absorbed water and cooled slightly.
Blend into batter.
Add raisins and All-Bran cereal.
Mix thoroughly. Refrigerate batter, covered.
Keeps up to 5 weeks.
When ready to use, dip batter from container without stirring into muffin tins. Use Pam or paper baking cups.
Bake in 400° preheated oven about 20 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs with mixer. Add oil, sugar and vanilla. Mix together in separate bowl the flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Combine with first mixture.
Add zucchini. Add nuts. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes in 3 greased bread pans.
Cool on racks.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together and spread on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix and oil.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Fold in fruit and nuts.
Bake in greased, floured tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana pops
directions: Peel each banana.
Insert a popsicle stick.
Dip the banana in the chocolate syrup.
Roll in walnut bits and freeze for 1 or 2 hours.

title: fruit punch
directions: Defrost juices, combine with ginger ale and pour over ice block or ice cubes.
Makes three quarts.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix together margarine and 2 cups sugar until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, and blend well.
Sift together salt, soda and flour. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Fold in grated lemon rind.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans or 3 small loaf pans. Bake in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes.

While bread is baking, combine lemon juice and sugar; let stand to allow sugar to dissolve to make a syrup. When bread is removed from oven, turn out on foil or waxed paper and spoon lemon juice and sugar mixture over hot loaves.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast; mix well.
Blend in egg. Add flour and mix until dough is well blended.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface and cover.
Store dough in refrigerator at least 2 hours or until needed.
Shape dough on well floured surface.
Let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until light, about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Blend soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish. Combine beef, 1/4 cup soup mixture, egg, bread crumbs, onion and seasonings.
Shape into patties.
Brown patties in skillet and pour off fat.
Stir in remaining soup mixture, water and parsley. Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with potatoes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix with cheese, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with 1 package Ritz crackers (crushed) with 3/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts. Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes; do not brown.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together as listed and mix well as each is added.
Pour into two graham cracker crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: party punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl.
Put frozen fruit such as strawberries, cherries and other fruit of your choice.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on box.
Saute chopped onion in butter.
Add eggs and stir until eggs are fried.
Add cooked rice and stir until well mixed.

title: cheese pastry
directions: Mix dough with hands.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 1/2 x 2-inch sticks or use cookie cutter shapes. Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 12 minutes at 400°.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Place in 3 to 4-quart casserole.
Cover with crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Warm oil and spices.
Put crackers in paper sack; pour oil and spices over them and shake well.
Excess oil will soak into sack. Store in covered container.

title: brown sugar nut kiss cakes
directions: Bet egg white stiff, but not dry.
Mash out sugar smooth.
Add to egg white slowly, beating all the while with egg beater.
Add the nuts; stir in well.
Drop on well buttered cookie sheet small teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 15 minutes in oven at 350°.
Makes 24 to 48 cookies.

title: triple tier treat
directions: Mix flour, pecans and oleo together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Spread cream cheese and powdered sugar over crust.
Pour 3 cups milk with chocolate pudding over cream cheese.
Let set.
Mix 3 cups milk with vanilla pudding.
Pour over chocolate pudding.
Let set.
Top with Dream Whip.
Serves a bunch.

title: chicken alfredo
directions: In a saucepan, but butter, onion, garlic and chicken.
Let saute.
Remove the chicken from saucepan.
Add bell pepper and whipping cream.
Let boil for 10 minutes; add cheese.
Let thicken, then add chicken.
Let cook for another 5 minutes.
Keep stirring, then boil fettucine until cooked.
Rinse.
Add chicken mixture on top.

title: chewies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: betty's mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, salt, pepper, garlic salt, sauce mix and chopped onion together in skillet.
Drain. Place soft shells in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour half of the ground beef mixture on shells and spread evenly.
Spread refried beans over ground beef. Pour sauce or Ro-Tel over beans.
Slice Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese and place alternating cheese on top.
Bake at 425° until cheese is melted or in microwave.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix and spread over top of first mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and water together.
Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Let freeze overnight and take out early enough to make a slush.
Very good.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in loaf pan in 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion, bell pepper, soups and paste; simmer.
Cook macaroni; drain and add to mixture.
Then pour into large casserole dish and sprinkle with mushrooms and cheese.
Put in 300° oven until cheese is bubbly.

title: bean salad
directions: Pour over beans.
Set in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Stir once before serving.

title: linguine with asparagus, garlic & lemon
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil and 1 tablespoon of butter over medium heat, stirring until mixture is golden. Season with salt & pepper.

title: homos (chickpeas with tahini)
directions: Rinse and drain chickpeas and place in blender with remaining ingredients.
Turn on blender and keep mixing mixture with fork until well blended.
Don't get it caught!
Garnish with olives and a little oil drizzled on top.
Serve on Syrian bread cut into triangles or as dip with fresh vegetables.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Cream together remaining ingredients and heat until hot.
(Do not let sauce come to a boil, cheese will separate.)
Serve over cooked fettuccini.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar, flour and salt; set aside.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil margarine, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Add flour mixture to this after removing from heat and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour in sheet pan (well-greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: herb cheese crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough; separate dough at perforations to make 8 triangles.
Halve each triangle lengthwise. Spread 1 teaspoon cheese on each triangle.
Roll up from wide end of triangle.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 16.

title: candied fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and mix.
Stir in nuts and fruit. Chill mixture for one hour. Shape into 3 rolls and chill 3 hours.
Cut 1/4 inches thick.
Bake 325° for 13-15 minutes.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Cook cut up bacon and onion over low heat.
When brown, add sauerkraut and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a good boil.
Remove from heat.

title: boston baked beans and franks
directions: Slice the frankfurters in thirds lengthwise.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, make layers:
1/3 can of beans, 1/2 the frankfurter slices, 1/3 can of beans, dry mustard, catsup, rest of frankfurter slices and 1/3 can beans.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and crisscross the bacon slices on top.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Cook, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 90 to 96 squares.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix
butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring with hands.
Add flour and milk.
With 1/2 cup flour, knead dough, pinching off pieces and patting out thin on greased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until done.
Makes about 56 cookies.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix salsa and refried beans. Spread in large flat pan. Spread on sour cream. Mix avocados with mayonnaise, salsa and garlic salt. Spoon over sour cream and sprinkle on the cheddar cheese. Top with diced tomatoes and green onions. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: veal in lemon sauce(yields 4 servings)
directions: Cut veal steak into 4 serving pieces.
Pound until 1/4-inch thick.
Coat with flour.
Shake off excess flour.
Heat 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine and the oil in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook veal until tender and brown, about 4 minutes on each side.

title: cracker barrel grilled chicken tenderloin
directions: Mix dressing, lime juice and honey together. Pour over chicken tenders, making sure all tenders are covered. Marinate 1 hour. Braise tenders in a nonstick pan or grill to lightly golden in color, but not dry.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and peppers. Mix in flour. Add tomatoes, corn, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and 2 cups cheese. Mix well. Put in buttered 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Last 5 minutes of baking, add 1/2 cup cheese on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Roll pastry 1/8-inch thick.
Line a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together, adding pecans last.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate (350°) and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until a silver knife inserted in the center of filling comes out clear. Enjoy!!!

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in a bowl.
(I use the pan I'm making the meat loaf in.)
Combine all remaining ingredients in bowl, slicing or pulling bread into small pieces. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add to meat mixture.
Form into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie for angels
directions: Sift sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar very slowly while beating until smooth and glossy.
Place in well buttered pie plate, making it thin in the bottom and not putting it on the rim.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake in a 270° oven for 1 hour or longer, until brown and crisp. Cool on rack until cold.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Sprinkle
bacon,
cheese
and onion in a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Blend remaining ingredients in blender on high for 1 minute. Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: picadilli
directions: Place the cut up tomatoes in an enamel pot and pour enough vinegar over them to cover. Sprinkle a heaping tablespoonful of salt over the tomatoes and let stand overnight.

title: fried rice
directions: Beat eggs with sesame oil.
Scramble in large skillet on medium heat, breaking into small pieces and remove from pan.
In same skillet, saute onions until tender.
Add frozen peas and cook several minutes until peas are warm.
Add rice and scrambled eggs. Toss with soy sauce and heat until warm.

title: champagne punch
directions: Keep all ingredients in refrigerator.
Mix shortly before serving.
Freeze an ice ring from Hawaiian Punch with strawberries or cherries.
Add to punch.
This is a pretty Christmas punch. Double the recipe for a larger group.

title: no bake peanut butter munchies
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar, peanut butter and butter in a medium size bowl, using a wooden spoon.
Roll between palms to shape into small balls.
Roll half in nuts and half in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: almost goof-proof cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Top with frozen rolls.
Then sprinkle on the dry pudding mix and the brown sugar and top with the melted butter and cinnamon.

title: cranberry sauce from j. harris' kitchen
directions: Heat cranberries and Fresca over medium to high heat and let boil for about 1 minute or just until the skins pop.
Serve hot or chilled with turkey breast.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Slice or tear lettuce and place in wide serving bowl; slice green onions and scatter over lettuce.
Drain water chestnuts and slice; sprinkle over onions.
Slice bell pepper and lay over water chestnuts; slice celery and lay over water chestnuts.
Sprinkle frozen peas over salad.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream thoroughly and spread evenly over peas.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, salt and garlic powder.
Finely chop bacon and sprinkle over salad.
Coarsely chop eggs and sprinkle over bacon.
Cover and chill for 4 hours or as long as 24 hours.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Mix together well.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: nannie's favorite southern pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.
Turn down and bake 30 minutes at 325° until set.

title: harvard beets, heart cookbook
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, pepper, cloves and orange rind in a 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in vinegar and beet juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add beets; simmer until they are heated through.
Just before serving, stir in margarine.
Yields 4 servings.
Contains approximately 115 calories.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or larger.
Beat together eggs, mustard and milk.
Pour over bread mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning cook sausage and crumble over mixture.
Add mushroom soup and milk and pour over mixture.
Add cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: 14 carat cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) round, greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool completely.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add 1/2 cup milk, then alternately add flour and eggs, then add flavoring.
Add the other 1/2 cup milk with baking powder and salt.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: choco-dot pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add pumpkin, oil and bran flakes.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing only until combined.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts.
Spread evenly in a 10 x 4-inch ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Drizzle with a confectioners sugar glaze, if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice and Tang.
Add bananas and toss to coat. Add fruit and nuts.
Stir together.
Sprinkle pudding over all and mix together.
Refrigerate.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; drain.
Put stick of oleo in with a little milk and mash.
Add salt and cream cheese; blend.
Add sour cream, chives and garlic.
Make potatoes creamy for baking.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish; sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate overnight, then take out and let set at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place each breast on piece of tinfoil (enough to completely wrap the breast).
Put 2 tablespoons of wine and 1 tablespoon of dried soup on each piece of chicken.
Then dot with butter. Tightly wrap each in tinfoil.
Bake at 325° or 350° for about an hour.
May serve over rice.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in double boiler.
Add 2 1/2 cups boiling water stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Cover; cook for 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks.
Pour hot mixture over egg yolks gradually while stirring. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour into shell.
Beat egg whites.
Add remaining sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating until mixture stands in peaks.
Spread meringue over filling sealing to edges of pie shell.
Bake at 300° to 325° until meringue is golden.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Put yeast in warm water. Mix all ingredients, except flour. Add flour a little at a time, mixing slowly after each addition. Let rise 30 to 40 minutes. Stir down. Put in greased loaf pan. Let rise. Brush on melted butter and salt. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: country style pasta with ricotta
directions: In a large heavy skillet, cook the bacon over moderate heat, stirring occasionally until it is lightly browned and the fat is rendered, about 5 minutes.
Add the oil and onion.
Reduce the heat to low and cook until onion is softened and translucent, about 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: planters punch
directions: Ingredients are per 8 ounce drink.
Top with cherry; better if served with crushed ice.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Put oleo, water, cocoa and oil in pan; bring to a boil.
Pour liquid over sugar-flour mixture, then add eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Put the soda in the buttermilk, then add to mixture.
Pour in one big pan or 2 smaller ones.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oriental casserole(this is a small recipe.  double for company.)
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
(For double recipe, bake 2 hours.)

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onion.
Add chili powder.
Layer chicken, chiles, cheese and Doritos.
Cover with soup and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch with cold water in small saucepan. Add boiling water. Cook until thick. Set aside to cool. Beat egg whites to soft peaks. Add cooled cornstarch mixture. Continue beating until stiff. Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; beat until well mixed. Add vanilla. Spread on pie. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown. Turn off heat. Let cool in oven with door open.

title: onion soup
directions: Cook onions in melted butter until tender.
(Cook slowly, you don't want them to burn.)
Add flour and blend well.
Add beef broth.
(If using canned broth or bouillon cubes, do not add salt.)
Stir well.
Add pepper to taste.

title: rice, lamb and lentil soup
directions: Brown the lamb in its own additional fat.
Add 3 cups of the water, the salt and pepper; bring to a boil, reduce the heat and simmer, covered, 2 1/2 hours.
Wash the lentils; add to the lamb and cook 15 minutes.
While the lentils are cooking, brown the onion in the butter and then add to the lentils.
Add the remaining water; bring to a boil and add the rice.
Cover and continue cooking until the rice, lentils and lamb are tender, stirring occasionally.
The soup should be thick.

title: tuscany cavatelli(diabetic)
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; omit salt. Drain and set aside. Combine tomatoes, olives, cheese, oil, vinegar, pepper and garlic in medium bowl. Stir in pasta until thoroughly coated. Serve warm or at room temperature. Makes 6 servings.

title: angel wings
directions: Beat egg yolks in bowl until thick.
Add and blend sugar, salt and brandy.
Add flour alternately with sour cream until all blended.
Turn dough on floured board.
Cover and let rise for 10 minutes.
Knead dough until it blisters.
Roll very thin.
Cut into strips 1-inch wide and 4-inches long.
Cut gash in center and pull one end of strip through.
Fry in deep fat at 370° until light brown; turn over.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll both packages of rolls and form into a 12-inch square on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Press edges and perforations to seal.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: turkey a la king(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cook green pepper and celery in boiling water until tender; drain.
Blend condensed soup and skim milk.
Add green pepper, celery, mushrooms, turkey and pimento.
Add salt and pepper; heat slightly over low heat.
Cut toast into triangles; place in small bowl, tips up.
Spoon turkey mixture over tips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, in buttered casserole.
Top generously with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 10-inch dish for about 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hard candy(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar and light corn syrup in 4 cup microwave-safe bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 3 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring to boil margarine, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Beat and pour onto cake while warm.

title: dirty dessert
directions: Mix until thickened pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip. Beat until creamy cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Add this to pudding mixture and mix well.
Layer cookie crumbs, then filling mixture, ending up with cookie crumbs on top.
Use large bowl and put in freezer overnight.
Serve partially frozen.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Crush crackers very fine and mix with margarine in a 10-inch dish.
Do not make side crust; just bottom.
Chop the bananas on top of this.
Mix the milk and lemon juice until thick and add pineapple; put on top of bananas.
Sprinkle this with coconut and then add nuts and Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries.

title: cholesterol fighter
directions: Mix all ingredients
and store in cool place or refrigerate. Drinking one very
small
glass
a day will serve as a very good "roto-rooter" for the veins.

title: apple roly poly
directions: Prepare biscuit mix as directed on package.
On lightly floured board, roll dough into oblong 1/4-inch thick, about 10 x 12	inches.
Spread with honey to within 1 inch of edges of dough. Combine
spices
and
sugar; toss with apples.
Spread apples evenly
over the honey.
Dot apples with butter.
Roll up
like
a jelly roll; seal well.
Bake in a greased pan with sides
at
350° for 40 minutes.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: corn and noodle casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cucumber and watercress tea sandwiches
directions: About 2 hours before or early in the day wash cucumber and cut about 16 paper thin slices from it before peeling.
Set the slices aside and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate for garnish.
Peel the rest of the cucumber and slice into paper-thin slices.
Toss in a bowl with the salt.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Remove leaves from watercress.
Save some for garnish.
Wrap and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: apple and onion beef pot roast(slow cooker recipe)
directions: In a large nonstick skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray, brown roast on all sides. Transfer to a 5-quart slow cooker. Add water to the skillet, stirring to loosen any browned bits; pour over roast. Sprinkle with seasoned salt, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Top with apple and onion. Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours or until the meat is tender.

title: creamy sausage casserole with biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, crumble and brown sausage.
Drain and set aside.
In same pan, melt 6 Tbsp. butter. Add flour and whisk until smooth.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Gradually whisk in milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Add sausage, bacon, mushrooms, and pepper.
Set aside. In bowl, whisk together eggs, evaporated milk, and salt.
Melt remaining butter (2 Tbsp.) in skillet and add eggs, stirring until softly scrambled.
Pour 1/3 of sauce into lightly greased pan and top with half of egg mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining sauce.
Place biscuits on top of egg mixture with points up.
Bake 20-25 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: chicken crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Separate the crescent dough into rectangles.
Firmly press perforation to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup of meat mixture on one end of each rectangle.
Fold dough in half.
Press edges to seal. Brush with egg.
Bake on ungreased pan 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken with mushrooms
directions: In large skillet over medium high heat, heat oil until hot. Add chicken quarters and cook, turning once until golden brown on both sides.
Remove chicken; drain grease.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add mushrooms; cover and cook.
Stir until mushrooms begin to soften.
Add wine.
Cook until liquid is reduced by one half.
Stir in butter, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Continue cooking about 20 minutes until sauce thickens.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer in order listed and let sit overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: clear lemon or vanilla sauce
directions: Stir until blended.
Cook until clear and thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice or 1 teaspoon vanilla and a dash of salt; stir. Put into pint jar and refrigerate.
A good topping for gingerbread or apple pie, also by reheating and serving hot.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Slowly add milk and vanilla. Pour into lightly greased custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: cheese and tuna bake
directions: Place biscuits in pan (sprayed with Pam).
Sprinkle tuna between and over biscuits.
Dilute soup with the milk and beat until smooth.
Pour over biscuits and bake until biscuits are done (about 12 to 15 minutes).

title: stuffed pepper soup casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients except rice.
Cook on the stove for 35 to 40 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Add rice and cook for an additional 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine beans and chopped onion.
Mix remaining ingredients except bacon.
Pour over beans and place in a casserole dish.
Top with bacon and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over low heat for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Knead, cool and store in refrigerator in plastic container.
Do not eat!

title: angel food salad
directions: Break up the cake into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water, when dissolved, stir in cold water.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
Pour over cake.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes. Cut into quarters. Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Put in potatoes and coat well.
Melt oleo in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in a single layer in pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once during baking. When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: sloppy joes on a raft
directions: Crumble ground beef into a large skillet with the onion. Brown meat evenly; drain.
Stir in soup and ketchup.
Season with a dash each of garlic powder and chili powder.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Slice French bread in half lengthwise. Top the cut sides with the ground beef mixture.
Slice diagonally to serve open face.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oysters au gratin
directions: Pat oysters dry.

In a large skillet, cook and stir oysters, butter and garlic 3 to 4 minutes until oysters edges curl; drain. Stir in flour. Add milk; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in wine, parsley and Worcestershire sauce. Spoon over oysters.
Mix crumbs, Parmesan cheese and melted butter.
Sprinkle over sauce.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes until crumbs brown.
Serves 4.

title: southwestern bean salad
directions: For dressing whisk together vinegar, oil, sugar, cumin, oregano, salt and black pepper in a small batter bowl, using stainless steel wisk; set aside.
For salad, drain and rinse beans using colander.
Place beans in large colander bowl.
Drain corn, chop bell pepper, add corn and bell pepper to beans.
Chop onion and jalapeno peppers using food chopper.
Snip cilantro using kitchen shears.
Add onion, jalapeno peppers, cilantro and dressing to bean mixture.
Mix
gently. Cover and refrigerate 2 - 3 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Makes 12 servings.

title: broccoli frittata
directions: Cook broccoli in water until tender-crisp.
Beat eggs with garlic, cheese and seasonings in bowl.
Stir in drained broccoli. Heat olive oil in skillet.
Add egg mixture.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Turn with spatula.
Cook until light brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage relish salad
directions: Crisp cabbage, cucumber and celery in iced water.
Drain and dry.
Blend all the ingredients together except cream and chill in refrigerator.
Just before serving, stir in cream.

title: no bake peanut butter crunch
directions: Cook syrup and sugar until sugar dissolves. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Cook until creamy. Pour in corn flakes. Stir
with large fork until coated. Spread in pan or drop with spoon.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Steep 3 tea bags in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups sugar until dissolved.
Add 4 small cans frozen orange juice, 4 small cans frozen lemonade and 7 cups water.
Add 2 1/2 cups bourbon and mix well with mixture.
Freeze.
Make 24 hours ahead. Serve with Sprite or 7-Up.
Will be slushy.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; boil.
Mash and add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Use a 2-quart casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator; let sit 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Dredge apples and nuts thoroughly with 1 cup of the flour. Beat eggs and sugar together; add oil and vanilla, then dry ingredients.
Add apple and nut mixture.
Mix until apples and nuts are evenly distributed through the batter.
The batter will be thick.
Bake in a buttered Bundt pan for 1 hour at 375°.
Dust with powdered sugar while warm.

title: ruby vegetable dip
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
In a food processor or blender, whirl beets and reserved liquid until very smoothly pureed.
In a small bowl, mix with onion and yogurt.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
If making ahead, cover and chill up to 4 hours.

title: quiche
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix butter, eggs, flour, milk and seasonings.
Add cheese, spinach and onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Lightly brown meat; add onion.
Cook until just tender.
Add seasonings, beans and soup; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes; add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Drop potatoes in mounds over meat.
If desired, sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese or sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pear under the sea salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in pear juice.
Beat together the cream cheese and milk; add to jello with a fork.
Cool until partially set.
Mash canned pears (drained).
Beat 1/2 pint cream.
Add pears and cream to jello mixture; beat with a beater.
Place in mold or bowl.
Before serving, top with maraschino cherries.

title: cornbread salad(very good)
directions: Bake
corn bread according to package directions.
Cool. Finely crumble into a large mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients and
mix
well.
Refrigerate.
May
be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: ugly salad
directions: Cook rotini pasta.
Mix all ingredients and add to pasta. Add 1 sliced onion and 2 cucumbers.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Toss ingredients often.
Serve chilled.

title: oven stew
directions: Place above ingredients in a roaster and sprinkle with salt, pepper and 3 tablespoons tapioca granules.
Dissolve 2 bouillon cubes in one cup water and pour over.
Cover and bake for 5 hours in a 250° oven.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Marinate breast overnight in spices and buttermilk.
Drain. Roll breasts in pecans and bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes then at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, milk, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Mix fruit with remaining sugar and pour on top of batter.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: diabetic orange whip cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk on top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks lightly and add to milk.
Stir milk, egg yolks and gelatin in top of double boiler over boiling water for 5 minutes until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly.
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Add cottage cheese, vanilla and orange extract.
Pour into blender jar and blend until smooth. Pour into mixing bowl.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually beat in sweetener and beat to a soft meringue.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Coat bottom of 8-inch glass pie dish with nonstick spray.
Pour mixture into pie dish. Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.
Top with orange slices to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: french bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips and paraffin.
Roll balls into the size of walnuts.
Chill 2 hours.

title: lemon bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine flour, butter and 1/4 c. of powder sugar. Press into an 8 inch square pan. Make a rim to hold filling. Bake for 20 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients (except for powder sugar) beating until fluffy. Pour and spread evenly over hot crust. Bake 25 minutes or until firm in the middle. Cool, cut into squares and sprinkle with remaining powdered sugar.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing real well.
Store in airtight container.
For a great cup of tea anytime, to 1 cup of hot water add 2 teaspoons and stir until well mixed.
May add more or less to your taste.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in pan; boil 4 minutes.
Remove and cool 1 minute.
Add pectin and few drops of food coloring. Pour into sterile jars and seal.
Delicious served atop Melba toast or round crackers spread with cream cheese.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach completely and drain off liquid.
Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve as a dip for fresh vegetables, chips, etc.

title: aunt ann's chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Bake in round cake baking tin for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 325°.
Use frosting of choice.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and egg white; mix well.
Add the raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until filling is set. Reduce temperature to moderate (350°); bake until browned.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: molasses cake(my dad's favorite)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Stir in molasses just enough to mix.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato bread
directions: In large bowl mix together all ingredients except flour. Knead in flour.
Cover with clean towel.
Put in dark warm place. Let double. Knead again.
Roll out into rolls and let rise again. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and stir. Shape into 1-inch balls and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashion apple cake
directions: Stir together sugar and oil. Add salt, soda and flour.
Stir. Add eggs, vanilla and nutmeg or cinnamon. Stir. Do not use mixer. Add apples and nuts. Stir. Sprinkle with sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Top with whipped cream to eat.

title: new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and peel off 1 strip.
Put in 2-quart glass casserole dish around edge.
Put in water with salt dissolved in it.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave 7 minutes on High.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Put margarine, parsley and chives on top (or dill weed).

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Heat margarine and chocolate over low heat until melted. Remove from heat; stir in powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth. Stir in water.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Pour lemon juice over bananas.
Dissolve sugar and orange juice in hot water.
Mix all ingredients.
Freeze.
Keep frozen. Slice to serve.

title: mystery pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in large carton of Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate and serve.

title: little smokies cocktail wieners
directions: Heat to boiling. Boil 1 minute.

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together.
Wrap brisket in foil after pouring on ingredients.
Bake 1 hour per pound at 300°.
Cool and slice cold across the grain.
Heat gravy and pour over sliced meat.
Heat in oven about 30 minutes, until hot.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet making one big crust.
Roll thin. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix dressing mix, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover with plastic or foil and chill overnight.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: coconut brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Add all ingredients together except sugar, then pour sugar over ingredients.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Do not toss until ready to serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine meat or fish, celery, French dressing, seasoning and onion in a bowl.
Chill 30 minutes.
Mix in the chilled macaroni; add 1/4 cup green pepper.
Moisten with mayonnaise, yogurt or additional dressing to taste.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter sheet pan of aluminum foil at least 2 feet long.
In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Boil to 280° (soft crack stage).
Add peanuts and cook until mixture is light brown.
Immediately remove from heat and add butter, baking soda and salt.
Pour onto the buttered foil, spread peanuts and brittle evenly.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: jan hagel
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar and egg yolk, then add flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Spread out on a greased cookie sheet (10 x 15-inch).
Spread remaining egg white on top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Stir occasionally. Save part for topping.

title: turkey dressing pie
directions: In large bowl, combine dressing, broth, butter and egg; mix well.
Press into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 10-inch pie plate; set aside.

title: new potatoes and peas
directions: In four-quart saucepan, cover potatoes with water (skins on); boil until fork-tender (drain in colander).
In saucepan, combine soup, milk, dill and pepper.
Add potatoes, peas and onions.
Heat over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: taco pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls over bottom of 10-inch pie pan to form crust. Cook ground sirloin. Add taco seasoning, salsa, water and green chilies; simmer. Spread refried beans over bottom of pie. Sprinkle 1 cup Fritos over beans. Spread meat mixture over chips. Spread 8 ounces sour cream over meat. Cover with cheeses and sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup Fritos on top. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: buttermilk custard pie
directions: In 2-quart saucepan on top of stove, add sugar, eggs and flour.
Mix very well.
Add milk.
Stir well.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Be sure to prick bottom of crust.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: green jello salad
directions: Melt jello and sugar in 2 cups hot water and set aside to cool. In large bowl, mix cottage cheese and drained pineapple.
Add Miracle Whip and prepared horseradish.
Also, add Eagle Brand milk and nuts.
Mix all ingredients well.
Add the jello and chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper, beans and 1/2 of the onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir; sprinkle remaining onions over mixture.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Serves 6.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix a German chocolate box cake as per directions. Pour half in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: chocolate-banana-pecan cream pie
directions: Beat 1/4 cup butter and 1 package cream cheese at medium speed with an
electric mixer until creamy; gradually add 1 1/2 cups powdered
sugar
alternately
with 1/4 cup whipping cream, beginning and
ending
with
powdered
sugar.
Stir in vanilla. Set filling aside.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Bottom Crust:
Blend together flour, confectioners sugar and butter in bowl; press into a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: brazilian cream with lime and rum
directions: Halve avocados lengthwise; twist gently to separate halves. Remove seed.
Remove avocado pulp and put in blender with the sugar, lime juice and rum; whip in blender until smooth.
Mound in sherbet or champagne glasses.
Serve garnished with lime slices or wedges.

title: lemon-tarragon chicken
directions: You will also need Pam or other cooking spray.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together the meat, crumbs, onion, bell pepper, egg, catsup, salt and black pepper.
Form into loaf and put in loaf pan (9 x 5 1/2 x 3-inch).

title: sourdough rolls or bread
directions: Mix ingredients; let rise until double.
Shape into rolls or loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° to 400° until done (bake rolls about 20 minutes).
Makes 6 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and egg and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll in small balls; place two inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° about ten minutes.
Instead of rolling in balls, drop by teaspoons.

title: squash and onions
directions: Cut squash into 2-inch pieces.
Heat the oil in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add the onions.
Saute until transparent.
Add the squash and oregano.
Saute for another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the broth or water and salt.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook for 25 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter.
Brown meat and onions in butter.
Combine all ingredients except sour cream and cook until meat is tender (1 to 2 hours).
Add sour cream; stir to mix well.
Serve warm over cooked noodles.

title: hobo bread
directions: Combine water, raisins and soda.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Next day, add other ingredients.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir in milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry. Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Keep leftovers refrigerated. Makes 1 (8 or 9-inch) pie.

title: punch
directions: Mix punch, ginger ale and 7-Up in bowl ahead of time. Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, put in frozen mold, sherbet, cherries and oranges.
Have a can of frozen orange juice or lemonade mixed to add if needed.

title: twinkie torte
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together and add egg yolks one at a time, then heat well and cool.
Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise and line bottom of pan.
Beat egg whites stiff and add to chocolate mixture.
Whip stiff the whipping cream and fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour over Twinkies and top with chocolate jimmies or your option of cherries, etc.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce in bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in baking dish and bake at 400° until slightly brown.
Mix remaining tablespoon Worcestershire sauce with remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve meatballs with sauce.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: easy butter cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine until it looks like whip cream.
Add sugar and beat.
Add flour, little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Beat.
With teaspoon, put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes (350° oven) until a little golden brown.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Shred the cabbage and add salt. Allow to stand for 1 hour. Squeeze out liquid. Add green pepper and carrots. Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed and boil 1 minute. Allow syrup to cool.
Pour over the shredded mixture. Will keep in refrigerator in covered bowl about 3 weeks or in freezer for several months.

title: easy cookies
directions: You can use any flavor cake mix, except angel food.

title: yankee noodle bake
directions: Brown franks and cook onion in butter until tender.
Combine with noodles, soup, water and mustard in casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces and broil in butter until soft. Cut chicken in small pieces and cook until done. Boil rice in chicken broth and let stand for 5 minutes. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder. Mix together and put soy sauce over mixture.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic Ziploc bag, add vegetables, oil and soup mix.
Shake well to coat.
Empty bag into shallow roasting pan.
Bake for 20 minutes, stirring once, or until vegetables are tender.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Beat in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: mayonnaise cake(the pastor's favorite)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add flour, warm water and mayonnaise alternately.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Ice top after cooled.

title: fruit dip #2
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise and Marshmallow Creme. Stir in ginger and orange peel. Mix, chill and serve with apple slices, orange wedges, berries, pineapple chunks, pears, etc. Enjoy!

title: tasty ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: macaroni with cauliflower
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set aside.
In a large skillet, put olive oil.
Add diced onions and garlic after simmering.
Add cauliflower until cooked, depending on size.
Either add macaroni and sauce or mix together in another serving dish and pepper to taste.
Serve with sprinkled Locatelli, if desired.

title: peanut butter bread pudding
directions: Combine milk, sugar and peanut butter. Beat with eggbeater until smooth.
Heat on low to scalding.
Add gradually to the beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir well.
Add bread pieces and mix well.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish. Set in a pan of hot water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm or cold.
Very good.
Makes 6 servings.

title: molasses crisps
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the egg; beat well.
Stir in the molasses; mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar.
Put on cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Bake for 12 minutes in a 350° oven (or until golden brown).

title: caramel chocolate brownies
directions: In a saucepan, cook caramel and add 1/3 cup evaporated milk on low.
Set aside.
In a bowl, mix cake mix, margarine, 2 eggs and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Press 1/2 dough in a greased and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: ham and pretzel teasers
directions: Shape into about 3 dozen small balls and roll in 1/2 cup ground pecans.
Chill until serving time, then insert a pretzel stick.

title: rosemary's sausage broccoli balls
directions: In microwave, cook sausage until well done, then cook broccoli.
In small pan, fry very finely sliced onion.
Add a little margarine to prevent sticking.
Chop sausage into little pieces.
Chop broccoli into smaller pieces.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients 20 minutes.
Put sliced dills in hot jars with 1/4 teaspoon of dill on top.
Fill with juice and seal.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter together.
Add beaten eggs, milk, nutmeg, vanilla, raisins and the cubed bread. Stir to mix.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake for 1 hour.
Stir, mixture and continue to cook for 1 hour more.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding and set aside until firm.
Fold in Cool Whip. Drain fruit cocktail, cherries and pineapple.
Add all other ingredients into pudding mix.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Pour in pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jean's jambalya
directions: Mix together in large covered roaster.	Sprinkle with garlic powder and red pepper.
Bake at 375° for one hour, stirring once after 30 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and cold milk.
Blend in softened cream cheese and Cool Whip.
In a clean flowerpot, alternate layers of cookie crumbs and vanilla pudding, ending with lots of crumbs to look like dirt.
Stand artificial flowers in the center of pot, garnish with gummy worms.
Serve chilled.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with beaters.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with favorite icing.

title: almond roca
directions: Use wooden spoon for stirring and cooking in heavy iron or aluminum skillet.
Cut butter in small pieces and melt in skillet. Add sugar; when well blended and bubbly, add almonds.
Stir constantly and cook until mixture forms very hard crack in water (almonds will be golden brown and mixture will darken considerably).
Pour quickly and spread evenly on cookie sheet. (Slides all around - I use my broiler pan.)
Cool slightly and loosen sheet of candy with spatula, then flip candy over.
When partially cooled, spread chocolate over top.
Sprinkle with nuts; flip over and repeat.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Slowly add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Add butter.
Gradually add egg yolks.
Cover pan and keep over boiling water, stirring constantly, until mixture holds its shape.
Add lemon rind and zest.
Cool and place in baked pie crust.
Put in refrigerator and make Meringues.

title: fruit filled bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy, add yolks.
Mix in flour and nuts.
With fingers spread half of mixture in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with filling.
Stay away from edges with filling.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cut into small squares while still warm.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and cheese.
Put potato mixture in lightly greased dish and dot with butter and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hot asparagus canapes
directions: Trim crusts and flatten bread with rolling pin.
Blend cheeses and egg.
Spread evenly on bread.
Roll an asparagus spear in each slice.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze. When firm, slice each roll into thirds.
When needed, bake at 350° until brown, about 10 minutes.
Makes a lot.
Can be made ahead and stored in freezer until needed.

title: white bread or rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 c. warm water then stir in 2 2/3 c. warm water, the sugar, salt, shortening and 5 cups of flour.
Mix until smooth then mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: skinny chili
directions: Finely chop pepper, onion and garlic in the food processor. Scrape into a 13 x 10 x 2-inch oval dish and stir in tomatoes, breaking up any whole tomatoes.
Cover tightly with microwave plastic wrap.
Cook at 100% for 9 minutes in a 650 to 700-watt oven. Prick plastic to release steam.

title: microwave tangy turkey casserole
directions: In an 8-inch microwave-safe dish, combine oil, garlic and onion.
Cover and microwave at High for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms, tomato paste, tomatoes, thyme and oregano; mix well.
Place fillets on top of vegetable mixture with thicker ends toward outside.
Cover and microwave at High for 10 minutes.
Turn turkey so that less cooked area is toward the outside.
Cover and microwave at High for 15 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: bird's nest pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half and cook until done; drain.
While spaghetti is warm, combine eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press spaghetti into bottom and up sides of a well-greased 10-inch pie plate with a spoon.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix with sour cream and spread over crust (spaghetti).

title: pizza
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Spread the dough and let rise.
After it has risen, spread the sauce on it.
Sprinkle oregano, basil and garlic on the dough.
Then put pepperoni and mushrooms on it. Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
After it's done cooking, sprinkle the cheese on top.

title: herbed garlic bread
directions: Slice bread, but not all the way through, leaving slices attached at the bottom. In a small mixing bowl, cream butter. Add Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic, oregano and garlic salt; mix well. Spread between slices. Wrap loaf in a large piece of heavy-duty foil. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: potato-onion casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and onions thin.
Layer potatoes and onions until all are used, in a greased pan.
Place slices of margarine on top.
Cook at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: 5 pound fudge
directions: Put first two ingredients into a heavy pan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 4 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
In bowl, mix the other ingredients.
When through boiling first ingredients, add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a large, greased pan. When cool, cut into squares.

title: stuffed italian mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.
Remove, chop and reserve stems.
In microwave cook onion and butter 2 minutes, covered.
In large bowl, mix ground meat, cheese, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, parsley, salt, pepper, garlic salt, eggs, chopped mushroom stems and onion-butter mixture.
Heat 1 cup water in the microwave in a baking dish for 2 minutes; drain.
Stuff each mushroom.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle tops with parsley and paprika.
Cover; cook until meat loses redness, approximately 5 minutes.

title: 1, 2, 3, beer rolls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Lightly grease a muffin tin and fill each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 to 12 yeast-like rolls.

title: chicken spinach bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in soup broth; coat with bread crumbs.
Set aside.
Combine sour cream, egg, garlic and flour and stir until smooth.
Stir in soup pieces, onion, spinach and half cheese.
Spread in casserole; top with chicken and remaining bread crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes.
Add rest of cheese on top and bake 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: hawaiian fruit cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in sugar.
Add dates, nuts and pineapple pieces.
Stir well to coat with flour mixture.
Beat eggs until foamy and light yellow (about 3 minutes).
Stir eggs and brandy flavoring into fruit-flour mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and paper-lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan, peel off paper and finish cooling on rack.
Keeps well.
Tightly wrapped, will keep up to 2 months.

title: german skillet beans
directions: Fry
bacon
until crisp;
crumble and set aside.
Saute onions in bacon drippings until tender.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Simmer
to 10 minutes or until thickened and heated thoroughly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Add to pumpkin mixture, stir in nuts and raisins or dates.
Pour into 2-quart greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes at least 1/2 inch thick, coat with seasoned flour then dredge in egg wash (egg and milk mixed well together). Coat with either type of meal.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
