directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan; stir constantly, cooking until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved. Pour over strawberry halves; mix well. Pour into pie shell; refrigerate until set. Top with cream. Serves 6 to 8.

title: glazed wieners
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot or double boiler.
Simmer at least 2 hours.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by tsp onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees until light brown.

title: cheese bread
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, butter and salt and cool.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add to cooled milk mixture.
Beat in egg, cheese, thyme, marjoram and 3 cups of flour until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour and knead well.
Allow to rise once in bowl and once in pans, covered, until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tortellini in cream sauce
directions: Mix butter, half and half, parsley, salt, pepper, mushrooms, peas and cheese. Heat but do not boil. Mix with the cooked tortellini. Serve with pork cutlet.

title: mom's mush
directions: Stir cold water in meal; add salt.
Add boiling water.
Stir. Put in a loaf pan.
Cool.
Cut.
Roll in flour.
Fry in hot Crisco until golden brown.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix together and make small meatballs.
Brown in skillet. Remove to chafing dish.
Combine 1 cup hot catsup and 7 ounces apple jelly and pour over meatballs.

title: olive spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Stir together yogurt, applesauce, powdered sugar, vanilla and cinnamon, nutmeg or ginger.
Chill until serving.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat, drain and set aside.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch or flour until smooth.
Stir in meat, Cheddar or Swiss cheese, onions or fresh pepper and salt.
Use pre-made Ritz pie shells.
Prebrown pie shell about 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Combine and refrigerate for several hours.
Roll in nuts.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter until softened; add sugar, pecans and flour.
Mix well.
Shape into balls, using about 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Bake in slow oven at 300° on an ungreased baking sheet for 45 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar when first taken out from the oven and then again when cooled.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator for 30 minutes before cooking. Drop by spoonfuls or roll into small balls and fry in hot oil until brown.

title: deep fried potato cakes
directions: Microwave potatoes until soft.
Scoop out middle and place in a bowl to cool.
Add all the ingredients and mix well until mixture is smooth.
Wet hands and roll into balls and deep fry in a skillet until golden brown.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix wet ingredients together, mix dry together.
Combine the two mixtures.
This will not look like "regular" cake batter. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Place 3 family-size tea bags or 9 cup-size tea bags in gallon jar and fill with cold water.
Cap loosely and place in hot sunshine for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove tea bags.
Serve over ice.

title: flap jacks
directions: Mix all ingredients and ladle onto hot greased frying pan. Serve stuffed with ice cream, peanut butter and jelly, bananas, sausages or anything you like.
They are just like a crepe.

title: baked bluefish fillets
directions: Mix cheese, crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cut fillets into pieces and dip into beaten egg mixed with milk, then roll in dry crumb mixture.
Cook in hot margarine only until lightly browned on both sides.
Put in shallow baking pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve with a little vinegar. (We prefer malt vinegar.)

title: shortcake for strawberries
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter.
Brown ground beef; drain, then mix in tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Then put all else in and mix.
Butter a roaster pan; put layer of sauce mixture, layer of noodles and end with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: perfect picnic broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli into small bite size pieces.
Drain water chestnuts and add to broccoli.
Crumble bacon into mixture.
Add finely chopped onion and celery to mixture.

title: select deli salad
directions: In large bowl, combine rotini and remaining ingredients; toss to mix.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato pie(recipe can be divided for smaller portions)
directions: Boil peeled and quartered potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain and replace in pot.
Allow to cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Mash potatoes together, adding eggs, one at a time.
Add enough eggs, until mixture has a yellow tint.
Stir in salt, pepper and grated cheese to taste.
Fold in cubed Mozzarella.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vegetables.
Boil sugar and vinegar for about 2 minutes, not any longer.
Pour over vegetables, mix well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours or longer.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all together, folding mayonnaise and Cool Whip in very lightly.
Let marinate one hour before serving.

title: fudge sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, Crisco, cocoa and water to boil.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon.
Pour hot mixture over flour mixture; mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° on sheath pan.

title: copper pennies
directions: Layer carrots, celery and onion in a bowl.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Will keep three weeks in refrigerator.
Drain before serving or use slotted spoon.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo.
Add cocoa, sugar, eggs and flour.
Mix well all ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, vanilla, and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until moist, pour in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste with 2 Chronicles 9:9.
This is a nut and fruit cake and should be baked in a slow oven in a tube pan. Try it and you will be glad you did.

title: jalapeno bean dip
directions: Combine all in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until steaming.
Serve hot or cold.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix together; form 1-inch balls.
These may be frozen for later use, or bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken curry cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover with Saran Wrap and chill at least 2 hours.
Shape into ball and coat with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Place rice in dish.
Sprinkle with celery, mushrooms, chestnuts, soy sauce, onion soup mix and water.
Arrange chicken on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crustless buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well greased 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Pour into buttered casserole dish; top with crushed crackers and dot with margarine.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Combine all together.

title: texas jalapeno cheese puffs
directions: *Olives may be substituted for peppers.

title: nanci's tamale casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a casserole dish, crumble up enough Fritos to cover entire bottom.
Slice tamales in halves or thirds and place on Fritos.
Empty the cans of chili into dish.
Make sure there is enough to cover the tamales.
Next, sprinkle the shredded cheese on top of the casserole liberally.
Finally, crumble up Fritos for the top layer and bake in oven for 25 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix eggs and oil together.
Add cake mix and instant pudding mix.
Add 7-Up, stirring as you pour. Pour into 4 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fried chicken and gravy
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Mix flour and salt. Roll chicken pieces in flour mixture.
Melt butter in frying pan on medium heat. Add chicken pieces to pan. Fry until golden brown, turning pieces to brown on both sides.
When chicken is thoroughly done, remove from pan. Leave all the chicken bits in the pan. Pour off excessive butter, if any.

title: summer squash
directions: Boil squash and onion; drain and mash.
Add butter.
Beat milk, egg, salt and pepper, then add to squash mixture.
In 9 x 9-inch pan layer squash, dressing crumbs and American cheese; repeat and top with cheese.
Sprinkle dressing crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients.
May be served hot or cold.
(I prefer cold.)

title: pie crust make-ahead
directions: Combine the flour and salt into large covered bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Beat egg with 1 cup cold water and vinegar; stir into flour mixture with a large fork gradually. Divide into 3 portions.
Store in refrigerator in tightly covered bowl until needed.

title: strawberry banana pie
directions: Mix thawed strawberries, 1 1/4 cups of sugar, flour and water. Cook until thick.
Place in a cool place until rest of pie is ready.
Cut bananas into small pieces.
Pour lemon juice over them and stir.
Let sit until cream cheese is ready.

title: fireman's stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix together the two cans of soup and stew beef in a 2 quart oven dish (do not add water to soups).
Cut up potatoes and carrots and add to soup mixture.
Add peas, diced celery and diced onion.
Stir everything together and bake uncovered in 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Turn off oven and leave stew in oven for another 45 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: orange french toast
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, orange juice and brown sugar.
Beat with fork until combined.
Transfer mixture to a pie plate.
Dip bread into mixture, coating on both sides.
Let bread stand in mixture 30 seconds on each side or until thoroughly soaked.
In skillet or on griddle, cook bread in hot oil over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Serve with syrup.
Makes 5 to 6 slices.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix the first five ingredients.
Freeze to a slush.
Pour into punch bowl; add chilled ginger ale.
Makes 50 punch cup size servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta shells.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 of mixed ingredients over the cooked shells.
Mix well. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, pour the other half over shells and mix.
Serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans for 5 minutes with drained water chestnuts (sliced), bean sprouts (drained), minced onion and salt.
Arrange in 2-quart casserole in layers.
Repeat layers with mushroom soup, soy sauce, milk and grated cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Remove fat and cut meat across grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Sear meat, a few strips at a time, in margarine; remove from pan.
In drippings, saute onion and sliced mushrooms;
remove from pan.
Stir soup, mustard, and tomato paste into pan drippings.
Return meat to sauce, sprinkle with pepper, and simmer approximately 1 hour or until tender.
Add onions and mushrooms. Stir in sour cream, sherry, if desired, and Worcestershire.
Heat through, but do not allow to boil.
Serve with rice.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pecan chew bread
directions: In a 3 quart saucepan, melt margarine.	Cream in sugar; add eggs, beating well.
Add
other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: brown's fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken parts well and let drain.
Use deep frying pan or Dutch oven to fry in.
Pour oil in Dutch oven and let warm up well before placing chicken in oil.

title: julie's cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a graham cracker pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cheesecake is set.

title: quick peach pies
directions: Roll biscuits out thin; cover with 2 tablespoons pie filling. Fold over and seal with fork edge.
Fry in hot Crisco until brown. Can also use apple pie filling and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: In large kettle, brown ground beef and drain.
Add potatoes, onion, tomato sauce or crushed tomatoes.
Stir in water, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 1 hour, or until the potatoes are tender and the soup has thickened.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sour cream and seasonings; spread in dish.
Top with a layer of pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, green pepper and pepperoni.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave 5 to 7 minutes or until Mozzarella cheese melts.
Serve with nachos or your favorite chips.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Mix all ingredients together except spinach.
Drain spinach well and mix with sauce.

title: dream cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Can use less Cool Whip.
Freeze.
It will keep for a long time.
Re-freeze after used.

title: no-egg potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, allow to cool.
Combine potatoes and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Combine green peppers, jalapeno peppers, vinegar and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Strain through cheesecloth.
Add food coloring.
Bring to a boil.
Add Certo.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Skim.
Pour into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
May substitute red food coloring for green.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add half and half.
Stir until thick.
Add Parmigiana cheese.
Cook and stir.
Fold in crab pieces.
Heat 3 minutes.
Stir.
Toss fettucini with sauce. Sprinkle on parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix according to directions.
Grease and flour pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Place brownie mix on baking pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes until set. Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over brownie "crust."
Top with fruits and nuts.
Melt chocolate and butter together, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over pizza. Chill.
Cut into wedges.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Add cold water.
Place half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Layer the sour cream over the firm Jell-O and refrigerate until set.
Add remaining half of the mixture and refrigerate.

title: dilled shrimp with rice
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Cook and stir onion, carrots and pea pods for 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Dissolve bouillon in 1/4 cup hot water.
Stir shrimp, rice, lemon peel and bouillon into skillet. Cook about 5 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Stir in dill weed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla.
Add cake mix (dry), 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Cover; chill 30 minutes.

title: walnut chicken salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Dice the chicken and add to salad.
You can buy chicken strips already grilled or cook the chicken yourself before adding to salad.
Serve with raspberry vinaigrette dressing or use sweet/sour dressing.

title: mexican deviled eggs
directions: Slice the eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks and set whites aside.
In a small bowl, mash yolks with cheese, mayonnaise, salsa, relish, sour cream and salt.
Stuff or pipe into egg whites.
Refrigerate until serving.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Note:
I add one hand of water for each 1 pound of meat to mixture.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water and bring to a boil.
Drain and cool. Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and salt.
Add raisins and cook in double boiler.
When starts to thicken, add beaten egg yolks to a little of the hot pie mix in a cup, then add to mixture in double boiler.
Cook to thicken.
Cool.
Put in crust and top with meringue.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Blend soup, water, oregano and garlic.
In bowl, combine 1/2 of the soup mixture, bread, onion, parsley, egg, salt and pepper. Mix thoroughly with beef.
Shape firmly into a loaf and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove from oven and spoon off fat.
Pour remaining soup mixture over loaf.
Top with cheese and bake until melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Pour salt over cukes; cover with water.
Soak 2 hours.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Boil remaining ingredients.
Cool.
Pour over cukes.
Must keep in refrigerator!

title: cream cheese mints
directions: In a large bowl, with an electric mixer, beat together cream cheese and extract.
Add powdered sugar gradually and beat until smooth.
Knead the last of the powdered sugar with hands.
Form mixture into the size of cherry and roll in sugar, if desired. Place on wax paper and flatten with fork.
Let stand overnight. Makes 3 dozen mints.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Salt and cook chicken until tender and peels from the bone.
Mix soup, grated cheese and sour cream over low heat.
Line casserole with broccoli.
Place chicken on top and pour sauce over it.
Cook in 325° oven for about an hour.

title: diabetic tomato aspic
directions: Before you even make the chicken, buy boneless, skinless chicken breasts.
Fold them in half, original skin set outside. This is so you can easily trim all the remaining fat.
Put them in plastic sandwich bags.
Make sure there is no air in the bag and secure with a twist tie.
Put about 8 to 10 of these bags of chicken in a dated gallon storage bag and store in your freezer. When you need chicken meat, take out as many chicken breasts as you need.
Put chicken breasts in the microwave (remove twist ties as it is dangerous to have metal objects in the microwave).
Set it to half-thaw the chicken.
You can now easily cut off all the visible fat remaining on the chicken breasts.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put into 2 vegetable size casserole dishes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt
margarine in frying pan.
After melted, add rice. Stir occasionally
until
rice
has
softened.
Pour rice and margarine in
round
Pyrex dish; add beef consomme and the can of hot
water to
the
rice.
Pour Lipton onion soup mix over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tennessee biscuits
directions: Scatter yeast on warm water and let stand few minutes before stirring to dissolve.
Put flour, salt and sugar in bowl.
Cut in butter.
Add yeast.
Mix well.
Roll on surface to 1/4-inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter and stack 2-inches deep with layer of butter between.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: pot roast and vegetables(in cooking bag)
directions: Trim excess fat from meat. Rub roast with flour. Place bag in pan and sprinkle 1/2 of onion soup mix on the bottom. Put roast in bag and arrange vegetables; add water. Tie bag and cook in preheated oven at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: tropicale club sandwiches
directions: For each sandwich, spread a slice of toast with salad dressing, cover with cheese and tomato. Spread second slice of toast with margarine, top with coconut, pineapple slice and bacon. Cover with third slice of toast. Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and roll into balls.
Flatten with fork tins. Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine water, salt, sugar and Crisco. Stir until well dissolved, then set aside to cool.
This takes about 15 minutes.
It should feel just warm if you put some of it on your wrist.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Combine 1 cup water and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Stir in flour.
Remove from burner.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add eggs (one at a time), beating well after each.
Spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch glass loaf pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°. Mix pudding according to instructions on box.
Add softened cream cheese.
Beat with whisk (don't be concerned about small lumps). Pour pudding mixture into cooled shell.
Top with Cool Whip. Drizzle chocolate syrup on top in circular motion.
(May substitute with shaved Hershey chocolate bar.) Refrigerate.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cream cheese and mix well. Add fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream. Congeal.

title: gullets(french waffle cookies)
directions: Cream sugars with melted oleo; add eggs and mix until creamy. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Use well heated waffle iron.
Drop by tablespoon onto hot iron; press until lightly brown or if using Belgian waffle iron, light will tell you when done.

title: salami
directions: Mix well in bowl.
Cover well for 24 hours.
Roll into logs. Put on rack.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add mayo as needed.

title: chicken spectacula(country kitchen recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen before baking.

title: custard sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt well in pan to be used in double boiler.
Add eggs and cream. Place pan over boiling water and immediately add 1 pint of boiling water slowly to mixture.
Stir constantly until thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Pour sauce over rolls when serving.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Melt shortening. Add onion, garlic salt and meat. Cook until lightly browned. Add all remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat about 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Serve with vegetables, pudding, cornbread and milk.

title: easy zucchini casserole
directions: Spray a nonstick baking dish with cooking spray.
Add vegetables and mix lightly.
(Don't add water or other liquid.) Season to taste.
Sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crunchy and topping is golden.

title: honeyed yams
directions: Combine all ingredients except yams; cook until clear.
Pour over cooked yams.
Bake at 400° until brown.
(Delicious over baked apples, too.)

title: ants on a log
directions: For each serving, fry 1 slice bacon for 2 minutes on each side.
Split 1 frankfurter lengthwise, not cutting completely through.
Place one of the fillings below in the cut.

title: granny's grilled dessert
directions: You will also need skewers.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and dates.
Cook just below boiling for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes.
Stir in other ingredients and roll into small balls, then coat with powdered sugar.

title: sauce for cooked broccoli
directions: In small deep bowl, whisk butter into mayonnaise.
Add all remaining ingredients, whisking well.
Warm by placing bowl in pan of hot water.
Do not place sauce over direct heat.
It will separate.
Sauce may be poured over cooked broccoli or served separately.

title: easy cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: date-nut loaf
directions: Cut up dates and pour boiling water over them; add soda and sugar.
Let cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in a slow oven, 300°, for 1 hour.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 30 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients, except paprika; beat until just combined.
Spoon mixture into a lightly buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat margarine, then add other ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers or one 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sassy salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut roll
directions: Put 10X sugar in plastic bowl.
Make a hole and add butter, vanilla and milk.
Stir well with a fork until dough is together, then knead.
If it is too wet, add more sugar.
Sprinkle sugar on board.
Roll dough out with rolling pin, turning dough over so the rolling pin won't stick.
Spread peanut butter to desired thickness over dough.
Roll up and put in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Take out and cut in pieces.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend together the margarine, butter, powdered sugar and the 2 cups of flour.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Near the end of the baking time, beat together the eggs, sugar, 4 tablespoons flour and the lemon juice. Pour over the baked layer and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Cut into squares when cooled a little and sprinkle with powdered sugar when cold.

title: caramel layer squares(this recipe may be frozen)
directions: In saucepan, cook caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk on low heat, stirring until melted; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts. By hand or wooden spoon, mix until dough holds together.
Press half in a greased (Pam) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 300° and bake for 6 minutes only.
Sprinkle chips over baked crust. Spread caramel mixture over chips.
Crumble remaining half of dough over caramel mixture.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes longer. Cool completely before cutting.
Do not add eggs or oil to cake mix.

title: delicious coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Cream margarine and sugar, then add eggs and flour, salt and yeast alternately with water.
Beat well after each addition.
Set in warm place and let rise until double in size.
Roll out and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and a little butter.
Spread over dough, then roll up in jelly roll fashion and place in Bundt pan (greased) and let rise until full.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: moussaka
directions: Brown the ground round or sirloin and finely chopped onion with olive oil. When well browned, add water, tomato paste, parsley, butter, salt and pepper. Simmer on low heat for 1 hour or more until paste is thickened.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix sugar, water, spices and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook without stirring until mixture spins a thread (236°).
Remove from heat; add pecans, stir vigorously until a solid mass is formed. Separate each nut from mass, while still hot, with a fork.
Store in covered container

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Add enough chicken broth to thicken; I use about 1 1/2 cups.
I don't like it too thick.
Put chicken in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add cream sauce to top of chicken.

title: dripless popsicles
directions: Mix Jell-O and Kool-Aid powder. Add boiling water until powder dissolves. Then add cold water. Pour into popsicle mold and freeze. Keep leftover liquid in fridge (it will get slightly). Use to refill popsicle molds.

title: baked cheesecake
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese, lemon juice, salt and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Blend ingredients together.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Pour mixture into unbaked crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Chill, add your favorite fruit topping and serve.

title: strawberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix in pineapple (do not drain), bananas, strawberries and pecans.
Pour half of mixture in bowl and chill.
Cover chilled jello with sour cream.
Slowly pour rest of mixture over sour cream.
Chill.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix vegetables, chicken and soup in ungreased 9 inch pie plate. Stir remaining ingredients with fork until blended.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes or
until golden brown.

title: turkey-potato casserole
directions: Grease square pan.
Cover potatoes with boiling water in 2 1/2-quart bowl; stir in salt.
Let stand, uncovered, 15 minutes; drain.
Toss potatoes with melted margarine and the Parmesan cheese.
Press potato mixture in bottom of dish; top with broccoli.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: chick-n-que sauce
directions: Measure lemon juice or vinegar, water, salt, sugar and Tabasco into saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Keep hot for basting chicken.

title: honey bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup water; blend 1 cup hot water, oleo, honey and salt in large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm; stir in about 1 1/2 cups flour and beat until smooth and elastic.
Blend in yeast, eggs and oatmeal.
Add the rest of flour and beat until smooth. Cover and let rise in warm place about an hour.
Stir down and knead a little; turn into 2-quart round casserole dish.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 375°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from dish.

title: fruit yogurt salad
directions: Mix together yogurt, pineapple, honey and bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts and crushed berries.
Chill for 2 hours before serving. Yields 4 servings.

title: sam's sauteed mushrooms
directions: Put all ingredients in skillet and cook over low heat until tender.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook chicken and break into pieces.
Save 1 3/4 cups of the hot liquid.
Stir next 6 ingredients together.
Put chicken in the bottom of a baking dish.
Add broccoli; pour soup over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cornbread dressing; add slices of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: thelma's beef macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together. Add beans, tomato sauce and water. Simmer 1/2 hour or so. Add macaroni; cook on low until macaroni is done (stir a couple of times). Put cheese over macaroni. Serve when cheese is melted.

title: malena's sweet potato cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel sweet potatoes and cut into bite size pieces.
Boil potatoes until just fork tender.
Drain and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon (to taste).
Place butter in casserole dish and place in oven until butter is melted. Meanwhile in bowl, mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Add milk and mix well.
Pour batter into dish on top of butter. Gently add sweet potatoes onto batter.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar. Delicious served hot with a scoop of vanilla ice cream on top. Double recipe for a 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: chicken wild rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan; add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Slowly add Pet milk and then add chicken broth.
Cook until thickened and remove from heat.
Mix all other ingredients except almonds.
Pour into 11 1/2 x 13 baking dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 325° to 350° until bubbles.

title: sweet potato souffle with topping
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased baking dish; cover with topping.

title: blueberry lemon muffins
directions: Mix berries and 2 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Make a well.
Pour in wet ingredients and add lemon peel.
Mix until barely moist.
Add berries.
Pour into prepared muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with melted butter and sugar, if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans; combine butter and flour; cook gently. Remove from heat; stir in seasonings and cream; foil in beans. Place in 2 qt. casserole; cover with cheese, then with crumbs of corn flakes mixed with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk, stirring constantly.
Chill until thick.
Whip cream and fold in marshmallows that have had liqueurs added.
Add coloring.
Pour into a 9-inch chocolate crust.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple, including juice, in bottom of a 13 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle entire cake mix over fruit.
Then place slices of margarine over cake mix. Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes until golden brown and fruit is bubbling.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in skillet and drain well.
Cut up onions and mix them with beaten eggs.
In saucepan, combine sour cream, 3/4 stick of butter and Parmesan cheese and cook until butter melts.
Pour in onion and egg mixture and cook a few more minutes.
Add squash and mix.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Dab rest of butter over cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oreo fluff
directions: Mix all, top with reserved crumbs, freeze.
You mix the dry pudding powder with the other ingredients, reserving a few Oreo crumbs for garnish.

title: carrots and onions
directions: Cut carrots in 3-inch pieces.
In covered saucepan, cook carrots and onions in water for 30 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Stir in soup, 1/2 cup water, parsley and paprika.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Garnish with almonds.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: mamaw's banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar, well.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Very good!

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar together and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
In separate bowl, mix together Cool Whip and Philly cheese.
Place this mixture on top of cooled pretzel mixture.
Pour can of pie filling on top and cover with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare salad.
Add cheese and beans.
Just before serving, add Fritos and Catalina dressing.

title: jayne's hamburger casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Set aside.
Brown ground chuck;
drain.
Return
onion
mixture
to
meat.	Add tomatoes, sauce, pepper and salt.
Simmer on low while noodles cook.	Drain noodles and add to sauce.
Bake in casserole dish for 50 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with cheese and melt.
I use Cheddar cheese.

title: west virginia corn bread
directions: Use enough water to make it desirable.
Mix cheese, onion and peppers in last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
For a larger pan of bread, double the recipe.

title: caramel ribbon bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix and walnuts.
Stir in evaporated milk and the melted butter or margarine.
Spread about half of the cake mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle chocolate pieces over hot crust.
Drizzle with caramel topping.

title: beat the heat apple pie
directions: Mix sliced apples, sugar, cinnamon, flour and nutmeg in a microwavable bowl with lid.
Microwave on High 6 minutes.
Stir and microwave another 6 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Place butter on top of apple mixture and cover with top crust.

title: clam dip
directions: Warm cream cheese to room temperature.
Add part of the clam juice to soften cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, Tabasco, garlic salt, dill weed, onion powder and clams (drained).
Mix well.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake and let cake cool to room temperature.
Using wooden spoon handle, make holes throughout the top of the cake.
Pour canned milk over cake. Spread caramel topping over this, evenly with spoon or spatula. Prepare Cool Whip and cream cheese to desired thickness.
Spread this mixture on top of caramel.
Spread with toffee pieces.
Keep refrigerated.

title: turkey-cheese popover
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine milk, eggs, flour and Dijon mustard in blender.
Blend well.
Transfer to a bowl and stir in sausage, onion and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes until puffed and brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine.
Add soup and broccoli. Stir well.
Add cooked rice and Cheez Whiz.
Stir well and pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: In plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until evenly coated.
Put into shallow baking dish or pan.
Bake at 450°, stirring often, for about 40 minutes or until tender and brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for corn flakes.
Place in large baking dish. Top with corn flakes and dot with butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chopped liver
directions: Dry the livers on paper towels.
Saute the onions and garlic in oil until brown. Remove from pan and add livers.
Cook until they have lost their red color; turn down heat to medium and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Put all ingredients in food processor, blender (half of mixture at one time) or put through the fine blade of a food grinder.
Blend to a fine paste. Add more seasoning, if necessary.
Serve in small scoops on lettuce as a first course, or as a spread on matzos.
Serves at least 12 as a spread or 6 as first course servings.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pastry shell with fork.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15-16 minutes until crust is lightly browned.
Cool.	Combine sour cream and mayo in bowl. Stir in chicken, pineapple, 1 cup walnuts and celery.
Pour in cooled crust.
Top with remaining cheese and walnuts.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before cutting.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown pork chops on all sides in hot oil.
Place apple slices in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Top with pork chops.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 24 pounds turkey that has been roasted and shredded for sandwiches.

title: layered strawberry dessert salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Gradually blend in Carnation and vanilla.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat to dissolve.
Blend into cheese mixture.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm, about 1/2 hour.
Dissolve strawberry and raspberry gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Mash bananas well.
Blend into gelatin.
Stir in pineapple and strawberries.
Spoon and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Mix all together.
Put in crock-pot.
Add water to barely cover.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook 12 or more hours.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Boil 2 quarts water and the tea bags.
Wrap in coffee filter the cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add liquid to juice mixture.
Drink hot or cold.

title: cauliflower and pea salad
directions: Break cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Wash and drain.
In large bowl, mix cauliflower, peas and cheese.
Stir dressing mix with mayo and add to rest of ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Very tasty.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar together and add jello and water. Chill.
Fold in the rest of the ingredients and chill until firm. Makes a large salad.
